Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review:
Easy as ever to assemble instructions are very clear
My wife and I put this together in 50 mins exactly. Everything was included no scratches perfect condition perfect packaging.
Looks like we received a true gem right out of the box.
It's a great addition to my Inspire M2 home gym which is 4X the price of this. In my opinion the Power tower is very well made very sturdy very stable
I'm 6'2 174 pounds
My wife is 5'8 122 poinds. We have no issues using this product. I really like the angled arm rests compared to the competition this is easier for true CORE work outs.
The Quality is Superb and I can't be the only one who thinks the branding the insigina is dope lol.
My wife and I will use this for POST and during work outs.
The pull up BAR for reverse is perfect placement very wide however for forward exercises so if you are a TALL person with a large wingspan this will work perfectly for you. I also like how the tower is adjustable and once you find your perfect setting leave it there and tighten the ADJUST BOLT until you can't anymore so stability isn't an issue.
Hope this review helps y'all in your purchase decision to this perfect Power Tower by City Birds.
Also shipping was extremely fast took 2 days exactly to get here from time it was ordered woke up to 8 am with it being on my door step. Wow I'm impressed if your having second thoughts on this Power Tower don't just purchase it. You won't regret it..worth every penny.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: I was looking for a chin-up type of work out equipment for some time.  The equipment better fit in my basement.  However I don’t like to struggle finding out where are the studs to which it is supposed to attach.  Finally I located this stand-alone one for my son who is 11 years old and recently got started to be interested in workouts.  Kind of Christmas gift.  First of all I was worrying about this workout station is too big to fit in my basement.  I don’t want it to be too bulky.  But it needs to satisfy a teenager boy’s need.  It turned out to be just fine as shown in the picture that my son was working on it.  The height is easy to be adjusted.  Even better it is not too small either. I found I can even use it from time to time.  I am 180lb; it’s not shaky at all when I get on it.  So basing on my specific needs, I have to say that the size of this station is perfect for my case.Assembly was quite easy since I had my son help me a little bit. No power tool is needed.  Hand tightening is perfect.  It became a good project for my son and I  to work together and get things done in one hour.  I considered it is an extra merit of this purchase.  Overall my son is very happy to have it as sth he owns.The craftsmanship looks very good, and I have no complaints on those beautiful black powdered sturdy square pipes.Just a little reminder that do not forget to use those washers that are included in the package.  But the instruction doesn’t tell you how and where to use them.  But it is easy for you to figure out that the washers increase the local metal stabillity.  This is something that needs to improve.  But, it is obvious in an engineer’s eyes.  Overall it is one of best orders that I made in the year.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review:
When researching a product I, like many others, always start with the negative reviews. For consumer power tower equipment, they are all the same complaints across brands. With those standard complaints in mind, here is my evaluation:

1) The equipment arrived on time, undamaged and with all of the parts. 2) The arm, back and pull up bar padding was of satisfactory quality. 3) The instructions were clear and assembly was straightforward, though some women might have trouble getting enough leverage to tighten the bolts using the tools provided. 4) A common complaint about these products is wobbling, so I tightened the bolts on the base and the bottom crossbar using a socket wrench until the tubes dimpled a bit under the bolt heads. Assembled, the equipment was stiff and stable. For reference, I am 5' 10'' and 175 lbs. 5) the distance from the captain's chair handle to the rear frame tube is 15", which is plenty sufficient for my forearms. If you are unsure, measure the distance from the web of your thumb to your elbow. For pull up bar height, check the spec.

Conclusion: The product was what I hoped it would be. No complaints.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: While this product will allow you to do pull ups, it is hard to do high quality pull ups. The station is narrow and does not allow you the room within the handles to do pull ups with good form. The station feels very cheaply made because it is unsteady, very light weight, and constantly squeaks during any attempt at a pull up. Don't get in a hurry while skipping on research and end up regretting your purchase of this product like I have. Do your research and truly find you a good quality pull up station because believe me when I say --  You will be disappointed with the purchase of this product. It is below average at best.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: The gym has a really stealthy kind of look and the low end is pretty solid. There are some inherant design flaws that can make it a little dangerous as in the picture of the back support bar. I was corresponding with the manufacturer / distributor in China with several photos and gripes about the instructions. I purchased mine in October 2019. At that time the instructions had no pics or instructions on where the large washers go. I had the gym almost assembled and had to tear it down and put the washers on and put it back together. The washers are hugely important folks. If you crank down on those bolts, the nuts and bolt heads will indent the powder coated support bars. Couldn't hurt to even go grab some larger ones to distribute the pressure over the square beam. It looks like they've made some improvements but what I still see that hasn't been addressed is the one bolt on each end of the backrest support bar. Not strong enough for a large person. I blew the back right off of mine. The backrest support bar should really have 2 bolts on each side to hold it in place. I could have sent mine back but with the modifications I made, it's pretty solid. Sadly the manufacturer didn't take my advice with photos showing them the weak area. The upper half of the gym isn't as solid as the lower half but overall it's pretty solid. I'm 6'2" 205 so I'm a big dude but not so big that a support bolt should fail during a workout. Disappointing. Hopefully they have used a better translator for the instructions. I'm sure it's not easy translating Chinese to English but maybe pay a few extra bucks and get someone good. Bottom line, I kept the gym. I love it, but I had to fix it. Best of luck to you. Be safe.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review:
Cons-
1. Upper portion of unit flexes more than I'd like during pull ups, maybe I'm just too fat, 200lb here.
2. Padded arms (for preforming hanging leg raise) is substantially short in length (im 5'11") (see picture)
3. Ridiculous assembly manual. No efficient way to verify parts list before starting assembly. No mention of some parts.
4. Very small metal shavings, small small, like sand, all through packaging. Not a huge issue, just open all packaging over the box unless you want it on the floor.

Pros-
1. Easy assembly, even w/o a proper manual. As long as you have common sense and can perform process of elimination, your'e set! TIP: all 16 long nut, bolt, and washers go on lower body of unit.
2. Pretty sturdy, doesn't wobble, doesn't tip over (unless you're trying that is)

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review:
I don't normally write reviews, but I decided to take a moment to review the CITYBIRDS Power Tower.

Arrival and assembly: The tower arrived neatly packed with all parts and hardware included. I opted out of using the flimsy open end wrench and hex keys, and used my own tools for assembly instead. Assembly was fairly easy with IKEA-like instructions, taking about 30-40 minutes to complete. The only concern I have about the quality of this product is how the metal tubing 'sunk' in with fastener tightening. I think thicker tubing would alleviate this, but hey, you get what you pay for.

Use: The tower seems very solid during use! I'm 5'11" 155 lbs and notice no issues with flexing or fear a tip-over accidents (this was my only worry with ordering this).

Bottom line: I'm happy with my purchase and believe this is a piece of equipment that will be part of my home gym for a long time!

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: I wanted to have this put together as a Christmas gift but was unable to do that because the package that had the hardware had already been opened and was missing 50% of the nuts and bolts. I gave it 1 star on everything because if I cant put it together, it doesnt work.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: I weigh 195 pounds and found it to be jittery and unstable. I was worried about one of the two bolts supporting the risers (that support the pull-up bar) shearing in half during pull-ups.  The grip diameter on the high bar (the pull-up bar) is too small. It has a cheap, junky look and feel.(The claim of this being usable for a 400 pound person is downright ludicrous. I've got news for you: 400-pound people can't do pull-ups anyway. Eric Esch? Maybe.)How to return it? It's practically impossible. You can't just take it to the UPS Store, toss it on the counter and scan your phone. It would have to be disassembled and packed. I ran an ad and sold it for $80 just to get rid of it and make room for my new one. (My new one, after delivery, professional assembly, some serious mats, and taxes, will come to $1100. So be it. And no way would I spend that much sight-unseen; I tried it in the store.)

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: This is the worst gym set don’t buy when it arrived it was damaged and dented and when Assembled the whole thing shakes and feels unsafe I have all the screws tightened and secure but they’re still no difference, where you put your hands on dipping handle it’s extremely uncomfortable and you might as well not have put that tiniest sliver of Cushion because it feels like your working out on metal if I could rate this a zero I would.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: The main reason I bought this was for doing pull ups without a wall mount and it is very adequate for that. What I did not anticipate was how useful it would also be as a stretching aid. I deal with chronic neck and shoulder pain and this device is helping me manage that better than I have been able to for the last 10+ years. Never mind the pull ups, just grabbing the bar with one or both arms and lightly hanging/stretching-- it is a godsend. The grips that accommodate the knee raises help with this as well. Again, doing the knee raises is good, too! But the stretching aspects this device can help with-- perhaps it's a niche interest but I'm leaving this review for those in that market as well. A++ solid recommend

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: I ordered the Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar because part of my 2020 workout goals is to complete 100 pushes and as many pulls as I can do daily.  I liked that the product could support up to 400 lbs, which I'm not anywhere near, but it gave a more sense of security on it's construction.The design is solid, comfortable and I've been able to incorporate the dip station and an abdominal leg lift into my workout routine.I did have a problem with some of the parts arriving damaged due to shipping, and the directions were not exactly clear where to use the washers and what bolt went to what part of the machine.  I immediately contact their customer service, and I was able to get an updated manual version with much more detailed instructions.  In addition, they were able to resolve my problems on the parts which came to me damaged with prompt replacements.Hands down one the better customer service experiences I've had with a company.  I would full recommend their product if you're considering getting this machine added to your home gym.  Oh, and my kids (6 and 4) love being able to do pulls up too as the bar comes down closer to their height!

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review:
TL;DR - For around 2 bills it's a reasonable choice, built to support people who are a bit taller with boarder shoulders.

First of all... if you're debating buying a power tower, just go ahead and do it. I waited longer than I should have and now I've got some serious catching up to do on anything but push ups, sit ups, and body weight squats with gyms being closed. I looked into building something in my back yard, but with the cost of steel pipe, fittings, and 4x4's it's a bit cheaper to just buy something. This met my requirements, as something that could support my 6'3", 200lb build.

Assembly was easy for me, about 30-40 minutes, with having put together my share of home and home office furniture over the years. The only snag I ran into was the machining was a bit off on two of the bolt holes. Instead of sliding through the oversized hole, I had to force the bolts through by threading them through... if it had been further off it would have likely stripped them. The manual was fine, pretty easy to follow if you've put anything similar together before. The unit was nicely packaged, and included all the nuts/bolts/wrench/allen wrenches that were needed to assemble it. No damage, and good packaging overall. For someone my size, carrying the package up a flight of stairs wasn't a big deal, but if you're on the smaller side it may need easier to team lift or unpack it and take in a part at a time.

Stability is good, for a lighter weight unit. You can tip it up or to the side easily if you don't have any weight on it, but when actually using it, it feels plenty stable. While it's nothing like the really solid units you'd use at most commercial gyms, I didn't have any concern when doing exercises with decent control and form. For chin ups/pull ups, I'm not overly fond of how thin and lightweight the bar feels; I'd rather it be about 50% thicker (but wrapping it could fix this) and be heavier/made of thicker metal... it works fine, it just feels lighter weight which doesn't inspire the most confidence in it. If you're wildly swinging around crossfit style I don't think it would work well, but otherwise it's plenty stable enough. I have the unit adjusted to the lowest setting, which means at my height I need to tuck my feet under a bit when doing pulls. No issue there, I needed something that fit well in a room with an 8' ceiling and it doesn't impact the quality of the exercise.

For dips, same critique on the dip handles as with pull/chin up bar... thicker and a bit sturdier feeling would be nice. The width between handles works well for me, however for someone with a narrower torso/shoulders, it may be a bit far apart your liking. With the can't on the supports, you couldn't reverse them if you wanted to do so take that into consideration.

For leg lifts, the pads are designed for people with really short arms... if you grip the vertical handles and you have arms my length, your elbows are completely off the pads which is not a comfortable position. For me this isn't an issue, I found with the inward incline of the pads I can just skip gripping the handles and do the exercise just fine. If you're fairly thick and need to have the back rest all the way back, your legs will hit the lower crossbar. I don't see this being an issue for many people but it would drive me nuts if I needed it in that position. At

The push up handles are just a freebie... may as well have them there with the length of the frame in case you want them. Same thing as the dip handles, they may be a fit far apart for people with narrower shoulders, but I liked the position myself.

If you want to use this for band work outside of assisted dips/chins/pull ups, this wouldn't be a good choice; it's too light. If you want something your fit grand kids will fight over from your estate, this is not it, invest in an commercial gym unit made of real steel, not this stuff, and expect to pay 3-4 times the price. If you want a reasonable choice that ticks most of the boxes for a home gym, this should work for you.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review:
Did a bunch of research and happy that I went with this one.
FYI I'm a 5'8 male weighing 160 pounds.

Setup - instructions are all there just make sure to look at the pictures as well for guidance on where the washers and nuts go. Pretty simple setup overall but tough with just 1 person. By myself it took me about 2 hours, could be done in 30-45 mins with 2 people.

Actual tower is quite sturdy for someone of my size, doesn't tilt or shake when I'm working out.

Shipping: Came pretty fast and was securely packaged so no dings or issues

Overall very happy with the product.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: Poorly made. It’s obvious the company doesn’t check their product before they ship. I couldn’t even assemble it because it came out crooked.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: I am very honored that I can buy this. This is a very good fitness equipment. It is very rare for me to buy this. I thought it could only be used in the gym. Because I ’m lazy, I do n’t want to go out to the gym, so I bought it myself and exercised at home. This machine is very stable and does not tremble and shake at all. This can train my arms to stand in a standing position together and support me stronger Strength, there are other functions for me, this is very good, quite easy to use, and does not take up too much space, a very practical product.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: Over 25% of the hardware to put this item together is missing, so I could never put this thing together, and it is so big it's nearly impossible to return.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review:
Bought this due to the Covid19 issue closing local gyms.
I am VERY happy with my purchase.
I'm 180 pounds, 6ft and this is perfect for my home gym.
Assembly is simple, one small issue that I ran into was the labeling Left and Right. So I had to screw and unscrew parts twice. It is the Left and Right as you look at it, not as you do leg raises. But that was an easy issue.

I will say that this product is NOT crossfit grade, so ONLY REAL pull ups, dips, pushups and leg raises are achievable (using momentum to throw your 200 pound body up 6" isn't much of a workout anyways). This MAKES you stabilize your body, nice and slow reps with all exercises. Making the workout that much harder and better form.
Would recommend to anyone who wants a good home workout with proper form.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: The Power Tower frame is sturdy and seems stable. The seat to support the back and the arm rests are made of inferior quality. The biggest problem with this equipment is poor design. The arm rests are too small. The distance between the elbow and the hands is too short (not meant for an average height person. I am only 5'9"). So you can barely place your arm on the frame and be able to hold the handle. It results in poor form/ bad posture which results in pain in the shoulders and forearms. Might work for people in the 5'6" or less height range.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: Very flimsy, cheap looking, much skinnier bars than shown in the description. Arms rest pads very small and uncomfortable, cheaply made. Back pad it’s a disaster with a very long extension in the back extending way past the framing of the unit. Need to keep it a foot or more from the wall to avoid the stupid and useless extension from not poking through the the wall. It occupies much more space due to this terrible design for the backrest pad.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: This equipment is a nice addition to my treadmill routine. It lets me do upper body and abdominal exercises at home. I was a little concerned about my 240+ weight causing a tower to shake and wobble, however, this equipment is very sturdy and can handle the weight without issue. Assembly was easy except I had to read the reviews to determine where to put the washers. The size is perfect for my needs. It arrived in one box and only one crossbar had minimal scratches. There were no missing parts and I received an email from the company letting me know I could contact them if there were any issues.  It is fairly easy to slide it around the room as needed.  To do the chin-ups/pull-ups,  I did have to purchase an 200lb assist until I have enough strength.  At 5 foot 11 and 240+ pounds I am very happy with this purchase!

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: Best I could find in the $120-$180 range, better than what I saw in stores for similar prices. Shipped in about 5 days. Packaged very well, a few zip ties were open which made me think I had a returned item, but after unboxing everything it all seemed new and unused. No strange odors or metal shavings, no rust or broken/scratched parts. Simple English instructions and all tools included, took about 45min to build but probably could have done it in half that time, it was fairly simple. The bolts aren’t labeled in its packaging, but they are metric and it’s fairly obvious which bolts go where as described in the instructions. The pull-up bar height is adjustable which is great for lower ceilings and fans, there is slight wobble in the adjustable section but that improves with tightening. The bar dip hand holds are welded in place which makes it feel more solid. The foam pieces are dense and low profile, they look less likely to tear than other foam hand holds I’ve used. I would buy this again for ~$160, my friend has the Stamina 1690 ($99) which I liked (light, simple, minimal wobble) but I wanted the option for more core work and I’m glad I did. I don’t think one is significantly more stable than the other, but this one appears more solid by design and is heavier. My wife was initially worried that this tower was too bulky but after built and in the room she seems happy with it (wife approves this statement, ha).

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: I am 5.9 and 230 lbs and been working out for 20 years in a gym environment.I need heavy weights and such. However since all the gyms are closed I was struggling to find something affordable where I can work out my back with wide and close pull ups. I ordered this and have been using it for 2 weeks.Of course I cannot compare it with commercial gym equipment. However I can do wide and close grip pull ups easily. Doing dips for triceps/chest depending on angle works well, and I do like the push up bar handles. Overall a good product. If you do not want to spend a lot of money I would say this works for the interim for me while my gym is closed.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: I think this Power Tower is a terrific product and seriously well priced for the quality. Delivery was fast despite the current stay at home pandemic slowing some shipments. I put it together myself in under an hour no problem using just the tools it shipped with. It's sturdy and hardly moves when I use it. I weight about 170 lbs. My space is fairly small and it doesn't have a large footprint, so fits nicely and I can do a variety of exercises on it. I can see how it might feel a little unstable for those above 210 lbs maybe, but the components are decent gauge metal and designed pretty solidly as far as I can tell.  I like that the height is adjustable too. Overall a great addition to my little home gym.As others have noted, the directions did seem a little confusing about where some of the washers should be placed based on the directions. I think best bet is to place them on the surfaces with only a single layer of metal rather than where two surfaces come together. A good example of this would be the bottom of the base supports facing the floor. I'm certainly no engineer, so could be entirely wrong about that, but the part facing the floor there is only a single layer thick. Supports on the base keep it off the deck and it hasn't scratched the wooden floor I have it on either.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: This pull up and dip station is nicely built and welded. It’s not a professional gym quality equipment for rigorously use, however, it’s great enough for anyone who love to work out at home.  I bought it mainly for pull-ups and dips. I am 165 lbs and  5’10. It works great and does not wobble. The adjustability of the arms, back and height is great. I love it.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: Disappointed in this item, some of the “predrilled” holes were not done all the way as seen in the photo where the armrest is supposed to be screwed in and secured.Pretty basic stuff to not do properly

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: Missing nuts! The Hardware cardboard  container was ripped open and bubble wrapped together.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: My box was missing parts and had no assembly instructions

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: After posting my review the customer service with the vendor has been amazing. They went out of their way to address my concerns and take care of the issues now and for for future updates to the product. raising review to 4 starsOver all this is just okay. It is built for teenagers or younger or people under 6'. I'm 6’2” and it does feel a bit wobbly when doing pull ups and the hand grips for chin ups are way too narrow. The bar itself is too thin for good hand grips and the ‘padding’ grip is very thin. If i can find something to wrap around these it will be better for me. The price on these used to be closer to 150 and under but I understand they need to take advantage of the pandemic. The leg lift is uncomfortable. The ‘angle’ of the arm pads is annoying and because I'm tall they are in the wrong place for the length of my arms. I'm keeping this because i need something and everything else was sold out. Decent starter. Not something you want long term in your home as an adult.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review:
Very solid and sturdy for this price. Not too heavy for home gym, but still sturdy enough.

It's very easy to install. Took me about 45minutes to assemble it with the basic tools in the package. I didn't even bother to get my own tools.

I am 145 LBS, 5'6. I have a 89Inch ceiling, since I am short, I set it to the lowest level. Very little shake when I do pull ups or dips with it. it's not a good idea to do muscle ups with it though.

The pull up bar width is a bit awkward for me. The wide grip is too wide, but the narrow grip is too narrow. So I grip the middle. But that's just how I feel for my pull ups.

I do a lot of rock climbing. One of my goals is to mount my Metolius Simulator 3D hang board on this thing. Wish the pull up bar can have a bit more features so I can find there possible mounting points. But that's not what this power tower was designed for, so I need to find my own way. Of course, my "Metolius Rock Rings 3D" certainly works.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review:
I like how easy it was to put together.

It’s Light enough that you can move it around with ease or adjust it some if need be.

All in all I’m really happy with it for use in my home workouts now. It adds just that much more variety which is great.

It’s a little shaky/bendy feeling but it holds my 275lb but just fine. If I break it, I’ll update this to let everyone know that it didn’t pass the “Platt Men Test” haha. My dad and uncles are infamous for destroying things you wouldn’t think could break so easily.

I hate the backrest and having to screw and unscrew something to move it. I’ll probably drill holes all the way through so I can just put a pin through for quick changes. Only a problem if you work out with someone else at the same time I guess. I just don’t like it and the back rest itself is chincy to me. Sounds like it’s breaking when I’m doing front leg raises.

P.S. idk why amazon rotated my photos like it did

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: We were looking for a pull-up bar and decided to try the stand-alone unit rather than in-wall.  We looked through several units and decided on this.  The unit is sturdy and well made.  I'm 185 pounds and feel very secure/comfortable when using.  Feels very solid.  It's not anchored to the floor so there is a little wobble but, nothing to make you think this is poor construction.  Everything fits together nicely.Took just over an hour to put together by myself.  Everything you needed was nicely laid out in the blister-pak.  Was pleasantly surprised when I saw the feet covers and handle covers were already on the frame.  Everything wrapped nicely for delivery and no scratches.  Instructions were pretty clear.  Only question I had was the left and right frames were identified but, not the left and right angled arm rests. No big deal, just took an extra minute to they can only go one way.  Would have been nice for them to identify left and right arms rests.  Nice to put something together yourself so you can see how well everything goes together.We're getting back in our routine and using all the stations now.  Everything positioned nicely for my 6', 185 lb body.  Like the angled arm pads for leg raises.  Very happy with this.Great Start for Home Gym

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review:
The hardest part about shopping for equipment is that a lot of it is designed for the fellas. I chose this tower because it had the design that would work for a petite person, was acceptably priced, and had reviews of a sturdy design and quality steel. When it arrived, the outside box was dinged up, but the parts inside were well protected.

Assembly: some people in other reviews have commented how the instructions are a little hard to follow. The trick is to read everything in the pamphlet first and get aquainted. This is NOT some IKEA set (and even those can be confusing). If you read the instructions -before- you begin, you'll be fine. Also, like with most things, leave the bolt nuts pretty loose! Just get them on there to start, because the last few crossbars will need some wiggle room to get everything aligned. It's probably easier if you have a helping hand, but I managed to put it together alone in a couple hours. One thing that can really help is if you have a ratchet wrench of your own handy when you go to tighten things down.

Use: I've been using the tower for 5+ weeks now and it's been pretty sturdy. The design makes it easy to get up and down on the pullup bar. If you wanted to make it more stable for pulling with bands, some sandbags might be good to add. One thing I do wish for was that there were some extra grip pads for the bar, since my placement doesn't fall quite on the ones that are there.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: It arrived well packaged for shipment, parts are well made and everything lined up perfectly for assembly.  It's stable, grips and pads have good cushioning and seem unlikely to fall apart any time soon, spring-loaded adjustment pin for back pad positioning is a huge plus since I have to keep changing its position between leg lifts and pull ups.  I added extra Wilson tennis replacement grip to the bare areas of the pull up bar, works fine and stays in place, and if you need pull-up assist you can loop a resistance band around the arm rests where they meet the vertical frame.  It's not gonna hold a candle to a Rogue cage, but for the price and compact size it's pretty darn good for what it is.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: All in all, the assembly was easy (took me under an hour, using the included tools), all the parts were there, and it seems plenty sturdy for my (135 lb) purposes. Really happy with the positioning of the arms for dips and leg lifts. I have low ceilings in my basement, and the lowest setting on the pullup bar lets it fit with enough space to spare for my head to safely rise above it.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: Wow, I can't believe I am now able to avoid the gym for the rest of the year and work out completely at home. I saw a friend post a pic of a power tower and of course I came straight to amazon to look for one. This had good, true reviews from people so I purchased. When it arrived, I was so excited to put it together right away. It is extremely easy to put together. This thing is sturdy. I have now incorporated hangs to my arm days workouts until I reach the ability to do a full pull up. (Almost there with this!) I am getting FAR better workouts at home than at the gym although I miss everyone. The customer service for citybirds is OUTSTANDING!!! If you have ANY issues, don't leave a negative review to vent your frustrations. Just kindly email their customer service and they are impeccably available, quick and there for you 110% which I didn't expect. Thank you citybirds for my awesome power tower!!

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: First of all: I am mechanically challenged. Meaning: there are many things that I am good at, but mechanical things, as much as I would like to be, I suck at that. That being said, this was one of the easiest items to assemble, I have ever purchased. It took me about an hour. And outside of putting the wrong arm piece to the wrong side at first; which btw I emailed customer service and had an answer in 15 minutes, it was super easy to put together. I tried some pull-ups and dips afterward, and it seems pretty sturdy. I also bought the 4 year square trade warranty, just in case. For $200 delivered, I highly recommend this item!

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: This is an item that will probably last longer than I do. I am 6 feet tall, slender 168 pounds.  I have no problem fitting the machine to the needs of my body and workout. If you are Arnold, you might have a bit of a squeeze. In fact, after a few minor adjustments I think I can leave it alone now. It actually blends in to the decor of my game room very neatly. Delivery time was reasonable considering it weighs about 70 pounds came from CA to MD. All the parts were there, easily identified, and the little tools they provide are all you need. Totally a good deal.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review:
Contrary to a couple of reviews I read before buying, these guys seem to have improved their packaging. All parts were included and not damaged. It’s not an industrial equipment like one you may find at your gym, so there will be some wobble. Plus it weighs no more than 60lbs like most other models at this price range so you shouldn’t expect it to feel like it’s bolted down

I weigh 190lbs and I did chin ups, dips, ab crunches, and pull ups without any issues. Barely noticed any wobbling. More so if you've got great core which can be improved with this.

I would highly recommend this piece of equipment. Was the last piece missing for my calisthenic workout.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: When the box arrived it had two holes in it and one corner had been crumpled in.  It looked like it had been set down on that corner.  I assembled the equipment and all of the parts were there and nothing was damaged.  Assembly instructions were fairly easy to follow.  I ended up using socket on a cordless drill to tighten the bolts most of the way then using a ratchet to finish them.  This really saved a lot of time.  I would defiantly say this is a two person job.  The Power Tower feels sturdy and doesn't wobble when I do pull-ups, bar dips or leg lifts.  I would recommend this to a friend.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: Video Player is loading.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review:
It’s a bit more wobbly than I was expecting, but I suppose it’s study enough. I don’t feel like it will fall apart, but I’d rather it not squeak and shake.

The hand grips for pull-ups are horrible. They hurt my hands a lot when I grip them.

I’m not going to return it because there are too many parts to try to disassemble. But I regret buying it.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: This is a very solid power tower for the money.  I purchased this mainly because I needed the height adjustment for the chin up bar since we have a short ceiling. It does adjust, HOWEVER, not as described in the details.  The specs claim to have 4 height adjustments, but it did not come pre-drilled for anything less than 78 inches.  So, I had add new holes for anything shorter than that.Also, the instructions suck!  Like really bad.  They are out of focus pictures with some bad line drawings, that's it.  No wording that would help.  Luckily, everything was included and all worked out in the end. After a few hours of headache we have a nice power tower.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: I cannot give high enough praise for this tower, in every regard except for one: the pull-up bar.  Every item was wonderfully packaged in the box that was sent, but to my dismay I realized late in the process of creating the tower that the pull-up bar was nowhere to be found.If I could somehow catch the attention of the manufacturer to get this one item, that would be awesome.  My hopes for that prospect, however are low.I am thus left with no other choice but to leave a 1-star review, as I cannot ignore the fact that I've paid good money for a tower which cannot serve one of its primary, crucial functions.You should buy this tower, but follow along with the manual to see if you have every component before you build it.  I'm not a lazy man, but my god... I'm definitely not going to DEconstruct this behemoth to send it back just for the pull-up bar.UPDATE, 7/5/20: 1-STAR to 4-STARI was sent a brand new pull-up bar as a result of their error, and provided $10 via Amazon refund.  I am truly impressed by their responsiveness.  I won't change it to 5 stars, as they should try to not forget arguably the most important part of the entire tower.  Nonetheless, if you have an issue, it seems apparent that the company will work with you.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: I really like this unit. It is very sturdy, and was easy to put together. I owned one before, and the pull up bar was accessed from the back. Since I have limited space, I like that everything is on the front. Like someone else mentioned in another review, the directions do not mention where the washers go. Make sure you put them on the head end of the 16 bolts.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: High quality device.Work well for pull ups, dips, and roman chair exercise.I find it very useful for building up upper body strength and becomes almost a center piece equipment. tower is tall so make sure have good ceiling height for pull ups. Push up handle are sturdy and greet range of motion full reps can be achieved.Dip and back pad hold up well mine has not torn at this moment.Overall. For the price.the quality is very good.I have had this about a week.and I absolutely love it!

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review:
Pros: I ordered one from another company that “oversold” their stock and then obviously didn’t get any more from their supplier so I got shorted on them meeting the delivery “window” 3-4 weeks all together. What was not nice is they knew they didn’t really have them “in stock” as stated on the web site. They were obviously selling them based on their manufacturer shipping more to them which didn’t happen. I ended up seeing that this one was “in stock” and appeared to be a slightly better made unit for 10 bucks more and delivery in one week. I ordered this one and cancelled the other one.

This one came to me a little late, supposed to be last Friday but arrived on they following Monday, no biggie there really.

Assembly was nice, instructions well enough, packing was A+.

Cons: My only complaint with this and it appears as with all the others I see on the net, now that I have used it, is that I’m a skinny guy and this thing is wide. Too wide really for me to use comfortably. When I get on the arms to do core exercises, my arms are not in close to my body and therefore supported under my shoulders to elbows vertically. My arms are out from my body about 35 to 40* which takes me considerable effort to hold my self up in that position as I have to use muscles instead of bode structure and alignment to hold myself up. So I fatigue out with my arms before my core which is why I really bought this in the first place, I can’t “hang” off a bar with my hands to do my core long enough before I fatigue out with the hands.

What they need to do is make the arms adjustable for small people. A quick cursory look on the net, I’m not seeing any of them with adjustable side arms that can come in to fit smaller width people. As I have welding and fabricating skills, it looks to me like an easy solution would be to make the arms similar to what they did with the adjustable back rest. Put the arms on a fixed “trailer hitch receiver” coming off the frame and allow them to adjust in and out as needed for the individual user’s size. That is what I’m thinking of doing to make this a lot more practical, but man what a pain when they should have done this that way to begin with. ;-(. That part gets a total fail from me but the rest is good.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review:
So far, so good! Was easy to put together, even with the confusion of having an intraparenchymal hemorrhage of the Subarachnoid layer making me constant confused.

Uh ... anyways, I'm a little over 200lbs and it seems to be holding my weight well. I'm glad I got it, as it looks like Gym access will be out for a while as the world burns from the Pandemic.

Therere are alot of options with the bar, and it does a good job of not taking up space. If you're stuck in a little apartment, this will be a good all purpose workout option for you without having to invest in a ton of weights, and weight for them to get to you.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: Overall I really like this power tower.  It's very well made and sturdy.My only complaint it's that the height lists as adjustable from 64-88".  The issue I have is there is nothing in between 64 and 81.  You're basically either all the way down or three different heights at the top.  I needed around 75" so I had to modify it myself.I do have to say I was impressed with their customer service.  The box shipped with two identical side riser bars that were supposed to be opposites.  I contacted the seller through Amazon and they immediately shipped out the replacement part.  It came to me within a few days.I'd definitely recommend this tower as long as you can deal with the height issue.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: Subject: Re: Return received for CITYBIRDS Power Tower Dip...Thanks, I won't give any negative comments to the seller, I have to point out the item is good in material, however, there is a big problem with the bottom crossing bar that most likely will hit and injure the ankle of the foot after finishing the pull-up action to release the body down the ground. My left foot hurts once. Hope the manufacture improves the structure of the item. Sorry, it is returned.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: This was a joy to assemble - easy to identify parts and no issues with the washers or threading at all. They give you all the tools you need and the directions are well printed and easy to follow (looks like they improved upon this based on prior feedback). I love the small footprint of this tower and it's very stable for both dips and pull-ups (I'm 165 lbs). Definitely would NOT work for TRX but is very stable on it's own. Great for a studio apartment and well worth the money.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: I've had this product for about three months now.  It was easy to assemble, takes up very little space, is sturdy, and has all you would expect in a power tower.  My only disappointment are the 3 padded parts...the armrests and the back support.  If the armrests were two inches longer (extended to the vertical frame) they'd be great.  I find that my elbows are uncomfortable as they hang just off the back edge of the armrest. and I'm a pretty average sized guy...not like I have long forearms or anything.  The backrest obviously didn't go through quality control.  It slopes to the right as the support bolt holes weren't aligned properly.  It still works fine, but it looks cheap.  I hope CITYBIRDS can have a chat with their supplier and get these small issues fixed...or get a new supplier.  Bottom line, I really enjoy this piece of equipment and would definitely buy it again...a great addition to my home gym.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: I find the dip handles to far apart as a result of the tilted arm rests - I'm medium framed 5'8" - probably work better for a bigger build. Be nice if the curved supports for the upright posts were squared off with a small foot rest on the top. Decent machine but compared to the last one I had this one could use some improvement for the price.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review:
Took me a good hour to assemble. Mostly because the instructions make it difficult to identify which screws and bolts to use where.

The washers weren’t mentioned in the instructions. I realized half way through that you need to use the washers for the main frame screws on the sides without an extra metal plate to prevent the metal from bending as you tighten the screws. I had to take it apart to add the washers.

I weigh 230 pounds and the unit definitely has some five when I do pull ups and dips. But it is very stable when I do leg lifts. It seems very stable though. I’m not worries about it tipping over. I think this will probably last for years.

The handles and pads seem to be really durable material.

The back rest is a little askew but it doesn’t affect the usability of the unit.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: The design has flaw and you can get hurt. The lower cross bar can hurt the legs unless your body was only moving up/down. But the body can have other movement. I got bruise on my leg when doing the pull up, and it was painful. I will need have some thing to wrap around it to prevent happening again.The cross bar on the bottom can also hurt your foot if you do no pay attention when landing.The material seems ok. But looks cheap.The design shall be improved.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review:
It's a decent piece of equipment considering the price. Could it be better? Yes. Is it worth the price though? Yes.

Pros:
- affordable
- easy to build
- versatile
- lightweight (though, could be seen as a con)

Cons:
- The pull-up bar isn't exactly ideal for someone 6'1:
The distance between my body and the center of the station is quite close and makes it a bit awkward/uncomfortable when I'm doing pull-ups. Specifically, the bar needs to come out further from its center mass, if possible... My roommate is 5'6 yet he found it to be a bit more comfortable. Though, I'm sure this design prevents it from tipping.
- The pull-bar bar attachment site is a bit sketchy:
I don't like the idea of having it secured via a fixed knob.
- Doesn't feel the most durable... (only time will tell!)

Suggestions:
- I kinda wish they had adjustment screws on the bottom frame (similar to a dishwasher) to help balance the station.

Overall, I think it's a fair piece of equipment for the price. Many others I've looked at are in the $1000 range, so this was quite nice. Though, I am curious to see how well this station holds up overtime.. Regardless, I think it's a good purchase so far!

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: This went together without a problem.  The measurements were listed, but we didnt look that closely, and we didnt have the clearance we wanted in our low-ceiling basement.  We used the drill press and put a another set of holes into the pull up bars, and now it works nicely in our basement!  we have four people weighing between 120 and 210,  that are using this almost everyday, and all really like it.  We all feel its built very well and super sturdy.  it was a very good addition to our workout area.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: After unwrapping pieces discover the very first piece, one of the support brackets, is off about 5%. This shoddy manufacturing made it impossible to assemble and it is going to be giant hassle returning

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review:
Pros:
-Low Cost
-Simple Assembly with all tools provided.
-Great Introduction to pull-ups, dips, push-ups, leg raises, etc.

Cons:
-Hand grips are thin and provide little padding
-Pull-up bar is thin and bends significantly for any weight over 180 lbs
-Dip bars bend slightly when under load
-For anyone over 6 feet tall, you will hit your needs on the rack when doing pull-ups

Overall: This works for smaller people, especially those under 200 lbs and 6 feet. Great as an intro into some of these exercises but there is questionable stability and sturdiness for anyone larger than that.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: Solid construction for the price; not thick gauge commercial solid, but just fine for a home gym. I’m only 5’ 9” so height is no issue, 215 lbs. so it does rock a little. Where the 2 short bolts connect the back rest frame to the main frame, they used a punch and tap rather then weld a nut on or simply just give you a nut; stripped easily. I had to use a punch to reshape the bolt hole and applied JB weld to ensure it stayed put. Prior complaints about the instructions seem to be fixed, although I did not use them and there seemed to only be one right way to put it together (dummy proof). Just be sure to use the washers where torquing will collapse the square tubing. Only other downside is that it appears they did not use vinyl for the pads, and elected to use leather made from human Bee Holes; smell is terrible and I like a new vinyl smell. B.O. soaked into it at a minimum.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: The item is solid for the price.Took 2 weeks to come and is not packed great, box full of metal sand and strong fish mixed with welding smells. Item ended up covered in tiny scratches from bumping itself during shipping. Had to drill out new holes on one side, I guess quality control is a little behind.  But in the end, for the price, it works quite well after everything.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: Item arrived fine in box however the item is missing bolts so it can’t even be completed. (Update!) Shortly after posting my review I received duplicates of all pieces, This Tower is very sturdy I weight 210lbs & I am very satisfied with my purchase I was just that one in a million it must be but the company was very thorough about it & stood behind there product extremely promptly I will be purchasing more from this company 10/10 hands down customer service!.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: The quality of this is pretty fair with what you paid for it. I’ve had it for about 2 months now and it occasionally squeaks here and there but nothing some lubrication won’t fix. I way about 175 5’8”-5’9” on a good day and it’s been holding up pretty well. My only complaints are the arm rest should’ve been adjustable. I would say I’m pretty average size and they come up just a bit short to wear I have to bend my rest to get my arms completely on the pads.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review:
This thing is STURDY, I have no issues. Setup- just open the box and its an easy 5 part processes. Just get those bolts tight!

Its super tall. I can even use the middle bar as a way to prop myself up to practice holding form for pullups.

I think its well worth the money!

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: I'm 6'3" and about 190lbs and there is no shaking or instability. When it showed up I was surprised by how heavy it was. It took me about half an hour to put together even though the directions are not that great. My only real complaint is the directions and the bar is a little thin for my hands but that's easy to take care of. Just don't forget to use the washers when you're putting it together, otherwise you'll cave in the metal around the bolt holes.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: I just bought this workout station, so I can't say much about the durability of its foam parts, but the steel parts seem very quite strong and sturdy. It arrived within three days of ordering. I put the whole thing together in about an hour and a half without help. I have tested it and it is quite stable. I weigh 150 lbs., but it seems to have the structural integrity and weight to support much heavier users. The workstation has been thoughtfully designed and the height and  lumbar support system are easy to adjust. I will update this review as time passes by.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: This piece of equipment is a life saver during quarantine. it’s sturdy and easy to build tools are included. it’s affordable as well. Very satisfied.Warning: this product will turn you into highly desired man so if you have a spouse that is insecure and jealous you might want to reconsider this order.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review:
I use thin in conjunction with P90x and it's excellent. I use this tower with bands and chairs and alone to modify the angles of push-ups pull ups, chin ups, and dips.

The dip bar pads could be thicker, and it's made in China so we'll see about the durability.

Overall solid for daily use.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: I am happy with the delivery time and assembly time and was impressed that the tools were included.It is fairly sturdy.  I weigh around 240 and I am able to use the Roman chair and dip station however using the pull-up bar is not doable as there is quite a lot of flex in the bar and the upper structure.  A lighter person could use it, however.  I am happy with it being a dip station.  A standard 8ft ceiling or taller is pretty much required as well. I could not use it in my basement which is just under 7ft. Overall I recommend it, the price is good and it is full-sized like a professional gym only not as sturdy.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: Looks just like the pictures. Strong, square steel tube construction. The padding is fine. Adjustability is good. Assembly is fairly simple. I took my time and put it together in about an hour and a quarter. The paint finish looks very good. The assembly bolts fit tight and strong. It is possible to make the unit flex if I do pull ups quickly but it is not disconcerting ( I have it set at the tallest setting.) No squeaks or rattles. No movement with the roman chair or bar dips. It originally arrived with two left armrests which are canted by 10 degrees. I contacted the company and they immediately shipped the correct opposing arm rest. Very good customer service. Friendly and prompt. I am very satisfied with the company and the product.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: Ever since I finished decorating my basement, I've wanted to create a personal gym, and this power towel is really an essential part of the gym. Generally speaking, I am satisfied with it. The height is just right and the quality is good. It is also very stable when used. It's been a while and it feels great

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: Originally after purchasing, the backrest knob came completely broken. There was also one screw that could not fit in correctly due to some defective piece.  The company immediately reached out and was very persistent to correct the issue and promptly sent replacement items.  They really went out of their way to make things right.  I appreciate the customer service.My husband enjoys using this at home.  Fairly stable with only a bit wobbly at times.  No issues and great for price.  I Like the adjustable height for pull up bar.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: My husband put this together in about an hour an a half.  It looks great in our basement gym.  We tried pullups, dips, and several other exercises.  This is going to really add a lot to our fitness regimen.  It seems to be pretty sturdy and stays in place.  I would buy it again.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: Great value! Packaging was a little beat up but it didn’t hurt the item at all so we didn’t care. Easy to assemble and surprisingly sturdy. Expected it not to be such great quality because it was one of the lower costing ones we looked at but great quality and very sturdy! Definitely recommend!

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: I'm 6'4", 240lbs and it's sturdy enough for me. I'll get some good use out of this. It was missing a couple washers (required a trip to the hardware store mid-build) which was rather annoying. The packaging that held all the installation hardware was ripped open with bolts/nuts scattered around the box.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review:
Just got it today and opened up everything. All the parts were there and everything, except there’s a manufacturing defect. The hole in which you attach the pull up bar to the frame is NOT THERE.'

Update: CityBirds was able to resolve the issue immediately and send out a replacement part within two days of initial contact with customer service. Really responsive and good staff.

In regards to the product itself, it is sleek and quite stable. The angled arm pads make it more comfortable to do ab exercises, etc. One note to make is that the pull up bar is a tad close to the back rest on the frame, so while doing pull ups you might brush your knees against it a bit.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: The item came in with a few small scratches and there was a missing piece.After contacting the company we received the missing piece SUPER QUICK and THEY offered to credit us a small percentage due to the scratches.The power tower is PERFECT for our home gym, it is very sturdy, hight adjustment is a PLUS!.In the end they have demonstrated that customer service is Key to there business and thats something I value. THANK YOU!!!!!!!!!!

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: Needed a cheap and compacted dip pull up bar for my workouts. This is just what I needed. Small, sturdy, cheap and gets its job done. Easy to assemble as well. I have been using this for a while and it’s very handy since I have a personal gym set up and I don’t need to head out to a local gym to get fit. The bar can be set at 4 different heights to work out different muscles. The product isn’t too heavy, yet sturdy and doesn’t make much noise. Definitely worth the money, didn’t regret a thing

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: The pull up bar is somewhat weak, but seems to work. (Im 200lbs). It doesnt feel strong though. The footprint and stability is good. Big downfall is the support brace in the center between the feet. Its placed right where to naturally put your feet down when done. Square tube doesnt feel good on bare feet. Just bad placement. Overall- medium quality. I like the tilted arm bars though. It makes doing leg crunches a lot more stable and comfy. It does feel a little wide for most, but not as bad as others ive had.Its not a heavy duty piece for full time use. But part time help, and kids can use also...decent for the money.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: The product was easy to assemble however it includes washers that aren't pictured in the instructions. I didn't realize til I was done that I didn't uses them because I followed the instructions. Other than that totally worth it and fits perfectly in my studio apartment.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: I bought this product mainly because it’s cheap and I could assemble this in my room or dorm. It’s quite sturdy, given that it’s composed only of thin metal bars. The best part is that you are able to do a full blown given it’s layout. I’d say it’s worth the money.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: So far I have used this 3 times since I put it together a few days ago. It is sturdy for dips and pull-up/chin-ups.  It could use better padding on the dip bars and a larger diameter or padded chin-up bar but I can get around that with weight gloves and wrapping tape. Virtually no wobble when I use it and  am 6' 210 lbs.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: After almost one month use it ,I would recommend this training power tower . When we received the heavy package , my 10 years old son very excited and ask for helps me assembly it . We followed the instructions done in 1h because it clear and easy understand. very easy to assume  .this training tower is very stable,and it's good quality and beautiful. My son and I use this power tower exercise body every day. Some times I hang my boxing bag on it  to training my son boxing , and the power tower also always in good condition . We all love it , this power tower is really a useful health helper .

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: This power tower arrived on time and in really solid packaging.  It took me about 45 minutes to assemble and the instructions were very straight forward.  It is but we'll and can support me at 175 lbs.  My brother in law, approx 230 lbs got on to do some pull ups and dips, and the thing looked kind of shaky.  For me at my weight, felt right butt not sure if it'll support the advertised 400 lbs.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: This gym equipment come with tools. Easy to install and good for home exercise . At this moment. My kids no school (because viruses 19)and I don’t want them going anywhere. This is one good choice.  I asked them to install it and use it. So far so good. Now we do exercises at Home instead to gym stations

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: Overall happy with the product. just a few concerns,  I wish the arm pads were a little longer as my elbow does not sit on the pad.  When I do the leg lifts, my lower calfs hit the cross bar on the return motion.  At first I was annoyed but my reasoning turned to "its better for me". It forces me to control the return motion and prevents my legs from swinging.  I have mine in the backyard.  I am using plastic garbage bags to cover it until I get some tarps to cover when it rains.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: I am not huge, 6' 1" 210 lbs. and this set does the job for me, some of the others were too short.This one is adjustable for taller people.Easy to put together, quality hardware & construction and I’m sure it will give me years of service!

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: Pieces missing including two of the rubber base legs

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: This was an excellent value. Works exactly like it should and is sturdy and well made. It was packaged well when it arrived.  My only complaint is the assembly instructions were blurry and looked like photo copies.  My husband was able to assemble it without issues but they were very if you aren't good with assembling things you might have some trouble

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: If you are a taller person you will need to use it at the highest height setting which capability does not exist in other models I looked at. Offset the balance with positioning the machine on a solid surface rather than a carpet and it works well.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: It's pretty easy to put together, it's actually lighter than I thought, but pretty sturdy, I like the design which allows for a couple more exercise rather than  just pull ups, it's been useful so far.

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: I've been looking for a piece of equipment where I can get a good upper body workout that goes not take up too much space or requires multiple pieces of equipment.This power tower is just what I was looking for! Sturdy and very effective at achieving upper body strength

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS

Product: Sportsroyals Power Tower Dip Station Pull Up Bar for Home Gym Strength Training Workout Equipment, 400LBS
Review: I don’t normally write reviews but due to purchasing this power tower feel it needs to be mentioned. Firstly I did plenty of research on other products available....after reading reviews I looked at what the negatives were....mainly that the product displayed was not the same frame size as seen on the photos.....this one had no reviews when I first looked at it but I did read the small print & it stated that the frame was 5.5cm Thick which being 228lb felt I needed a strong tower to take my weight.....I took the plunge & purchased it as it was sold by amazon & they are very good with customer service if anything was to be misold......it came within 2 days & I also noticed that it did in fact have reviews which appeared after I made the purchase to which most were positive.....some said that the only problem was when putting it together the instructions were not very clear as to where the screws went or where to put the washers.....I am no genius & managed to erect this on my own within an hour....to make it simple I removed the nuts/bolts/washers/handles & tools from the sealed packaging exactly as they were in the packaging.....the instructions give a size & description of what one goes where which made it so much easier just needs done concentration.....had no problems except one screw was threaded so just simple cut the end off & it was fine...now for the most important bit...the tower is extremely strong & robust almost as good as a gym product....it takes my weight comfortable & fits perfect in my garage.....I am getting no rewards for this review just felt that for such a good product it deserved the time to write this so as someone else can be happy with purchasing the correct power tower & not get fooled into buying one that states a different product delivered to the one advertised.....if you really want a good product then I would highly recommend this one

Review: I was looking for a chin-up type of work out equipment for some time.  The equipment better fit in my basement.  However I don’t like to struggle finding out where are the studs to which it is supposed to attach.  Finally I located this stand-alone one for my son who is 11 years old and recently got started to be interested in workouts.  Kind of Christmas gift.  First of all I was worrying about this workout station is too big to fit in my basement.  I don’t want it to be too bulky.  But it needs to satisfy a teenager boy’s need.  It turned out to be just fine as shown in the picture that my son was working on it.  The height is easy to be adjusted.  Even better it is not too small either. I found I can even use it from time to time.  I am 180lb; it’s not shaky at all when I get on it.  So basing on my specific needs, I have to say that the size of this station is perfect for my case.Assembly was quite easy since I had my son help me a little bit. No power tool is needed.  Hand tightening is perfect.  It became a good project for my son and I  to work together and get things done in one hour.  I considered it is an extra merit of this purchase.  Overall my son is very happy to have it as sth he owns.The craftsmanship looks very good, and I have no complaints on those beautiful black powdered sturdy square pipes.Just a little reminder that do not forget to use those washers that are included in the package.  But the instruction doesn’t tell you how and where to use them.  But it is easy for you to figure out that the washers increase the local metal stabillity.  This is something that needs to improve.  But, it is obvious in an engineer’s eyes.  Overall it is one of best orders that I made in the year.
