Product: BangTong&Li Power Tower Dip Station Adjustable Pull Up & Dip Stands Multi-Function Strength Training Pull up Bar Fitness Equipment for Home Gym
Review: For the price, this thing is worth it.  I'm only 5'6" / 155lbs and do not do many violent / cross fit movements so i'm not swinging everywhere.  But i do add extra weights when i do pull ups and dips (about 45-135 on a weight belt) which does swing a little.  Yes the structure does flex a little and squeak, but at no point do i feel like its going to topple over.  I also have this on very soft workout mats that doesnt help keep this thing sturdy.  Still not worried when doing workouts and i'm generally pretty cautious.I do also like that the structure is light where i can move it all over the place by myself.  However it is not good as an anchor for workout bands and it will pull the rack.  It never specified that this was the purpose so never expected it to fulfill that need.Would suggest if  you are on a budget or dont want to go crazy on a full home gym.

Product: BangTong&Li Power Tower Dip Station Adjustable Pull Up & Dip Stands Multi-Function Strength Training Pull up Bar Fitness Equipment for Home Gym
Review: Video Player is loading.

Product: BangTong&Li Power Tower Dip Station Adjustable Pull Up & Dip Stands Multi-Function Strength Training Pull up Bar Fitness Equipment for Home Gym
Review: This power tower arrives in package with the pieces arranged that avoids wasted space.  Each metal component is inside a bubble wrap sleeve at all necessary points with hardly any excess.  The nuts and bolts are bundled together in a resealable zipper bag and the three cushion pieces are in thicker plastic sealed bags.The black metal pieces have an excellent smooth coating finish with no rough edges.Thick Rubber covers the handles the cushions are a sweat resistant vinyl with non forming foam inside.Instructions are simple to follow with pictures to help you know which bolt nut pair is required at that step.  No additional tools are required when using the two included wrenches.  None of components had small scratches in coating or dents that might cause minor rust.  My time from unboxing to workout was under 30 minutes and that was assembling by myself.This tower has a nominal footprint and if you remove the two bolts to the pull part you can lower the bar to under 52” height.Found no significant “wobble” in frame when the two adjustments knobs are tightened and the threads are in the welded bolt so the pull up bar beams are not sitting on threads.  My weight is  198 pounds and am not concerned with tipping over.  The back rest bar can remove by easily pulling out the two ball bearing pins so you can do “toes to bar” which is a popular routine with my CrossFit WOD chart.The workout chart that is included indicates that this unit could equal anything a commercial gym but at a fraction of the price and the convenience of using at home especially during virus start at home.  I have connected a pulley with a thick nylon webbing strap to connect my lat bar kit to offer for additional muscle development.

Product: BangTong&Li Power Tower Dip Station Adjustable Pull Up & Dip Stands Multi-Function Strength Training Pull up Bar Fitness Equipment for Home Gym
Review: Cheap, thin extruded steel and missing hardware with no directions.You’re better off throwing that 100 dollars in a wishing well, hoping for magical muscles.

Product: BangTong&Li Power Tower Dip Station Adjustable Pull Up & Dip Stands Multi-Function Strength Training Pull up Bar Fitness Equipment for Home Gym
Review: This product might hold the weight of a 120lb person. The pull-up bar already bent after two uses. I would not recommend this product.

Product: BangTong&Li Power Tower Dip Station Adjustable Pull Up & Dip Stands Multi-Function Strength Training Pull up Bar Fitness Equipment for Home Gym
Review: I wouldn't recommend this for a serious lifter or for a serious home-gym build, but if you need something to knock out pull-ups, dips, ab work, and pushups then this is a great option.  Product is pretty sturdy, but after a month of daily use I had to adjust it about once every week or so to ensure all of the parts remained tightly fit together.  Probably perfect for a secondary gym option, quarantine at-home option, or perhaps a college-dorm setting.  Again, this is not sturdy or legitimate enough for a serious home-gym build, but surely good enough for an easy at-home option when in a pinch or needing to get extra reps in throughout the day without heading to the gym a second or third time.  Hope that helps!

Product: BangTong&Li Power Tower Dip Station Adjustable Pull Up & Dip Stands Multi-Function Strength Training Pull up Bar Fitness Equipment for Home Gym
Review: It's extremely narrow.  The depth available to actually do a pull up in is very shallow (don't plan to raise your knees at all.  Even completely tightened down down, the upper bar has a good inch or so of forward and backward sway to it, because of the way the 90 degree braces at the bottom are, and the because of the forward and backwards play in the adjustable height bars.  It's also very light and easy to tip.  a couple of pounds pressure to the side anywhere above about the halfway point, and it starts to come off the ground.

Product: BangTong&Li Power Tower Dip Station Adjustable Pull Up & Dip Stands Multi-Function Strength Training Pull up Bar Fitness Equipment for Home Gym
Review: Solid product that was pretty easy to assemble. Just get the bolts in order of size and you'll figure it out, directions could be bigger print though. After assembling, its solid! Easy to move around for relocation, and no wobble. Height adjustment is a nice feature for sizing to the room/person. Product: WINNOW Adjustable Weight Bench Foldable Home Exercise Gym Workout Bench Incline Decline Flat Bench Press for Full Body Workout
Review:
I’ve been enjoying using this and learning all the different ways you can use them; I definitely feel more motivated to work out when I’ve got the proper equipment! It came packed nicely in a mid-sized box and setup was very straightforward with easy to read instructions. Each of the parts were easily identifiable and the nuts and bolts were organised and labelled very well on a shrink-wrapped piece of card. It took around 35 minutes to build by myself taking my time to do it properly.

Once built, the bench feels very solid and doesn’t rattle or move around. Both the base and back are made from easy to clean PU leather and are surprisingly comfortable with plenty of cushioning. The foam rollers on the leg hold down are thick enough to put pressure on without feeling the bar inside. The back has 6 adjustments and the seat has 4, both are easy to move and firmly stay in place when set in position. The whole thing collapses into a more compact size that should fit under your bed; just fold the back down, pull the seat and frame pin out, unscrew the leg hold down and fold the unit together which takes less than a minute to do altogether.

Overall, I think everything about it is good quality and it was easy to build with a good set of instructions. There loads of exercises you can use it for, and it would make a useful addition to your home workout collection. I feel its competitively priced for what you get and I’m very happy to recommend this item!

Product: WINNOW Adjustable Weight Bench Foldable Home Exercise Gym Workout Bench Incline Decline Flat Bench Press for Full Body Workout
Review:
I've not owned a weight bench before but I've used plenty when going to the gym where I made the most of them.

This arrived in a large box and was quite heavy to move.

As someone who likes to assemble things, this weight bench took me about 15 minutes to fully assemble while trying to read the instructions at the same time and getting distracted by friends who thought they didn't need any instructions!

This feels very sturdy and is capable of withstanding a lot of weight on it - it won't collapse on itself. When on the weight bench itself, it feels comfortable for the most part and when I lean back onto it, my back feels supported.
However, the quality is noticeably different from the ones at the gym - it's not as good but still does the job as best it can.

As mine is on carpet, I have little worry about it slipping but there are rubber grips for added security - it can be set up on different types of surfaces such as carpet, vinyl, wooden floorboards etc.

It is adjustable which allows it to be used for a variety of work outs - making it easier to stay fit in your own home. From setting it up at an incline to having it completely flat, this weight bench is definitely suitable for this.

One thing I love about this is that it folds up - as these weight benches take up so much space (which I don't have much of), it is a huge relief that I can just fold this up and store it away. When it needs to be used, I can unfold it, use it for as long as required, then store it away again - allowing me to make the most of the limited space I have.

Perfect for those wanting to set up a home gym - shake the dust off those dumbbells and barbells and start getting that summer body!

If this was helpful, please tap that helpful button below - Cheers!

Review: I've used this for a couple of weeks now within my new year efforts to keep up with my fitness and up my game a little now I get to spend much less time at the gym and it;s been a great motivator. My partner put it together for me, one because he's much better with these things and 2 because he uses all sorts of different benches at the gym, but I helped and to be honest could easily have done it myself following the instructions. It's good quality overall and pretty solid once put together and tightened and certainly solid enough for my lighter needs. Product: WINNOW Adjustable Weight Bench Foldable Home Exercise Gym Workout Bench Incline Decline Flat Bench Press for Full Body Workout
Review:
If you’re a reasonably adept flat-pack assembler then putting this WINNOW Adjustable Weight Incline/Decline Bench together shouldn’t be too much of a challenge. There’s an illustrated step-by-step guide included and it’s reasonably straightforward and takes about 20 minutes. Once together you’ve got a sturdy and quite well finished incline bench that wouldn’t win any design prizes but is stable and functional. The padded seat and back panels are comfortable and have a decent vinyl covering. The back of the panels is less well finished with a non-woven fabric just stapled in place, but you don’t see that in use (or the photo’s) so maybe it’s not a big deal.

You can adjust the back through a wide range of preset angles, including dropping it to get a decline bench for ab’ work. It’s easy to change the angle by just moving the prop from one retainer to the next and there’s no lock or key needed. The seat and padded leg brace are also adjustable but more awkward to set and you have to either use a push-in rod or a screw-knob to lock them into place. The bench folds more flat when not in use so you can slide it under a bed or put it into a cupboard. You’ll need a decent amount of clearance around it when in use, probably about the same area as a king-size bed, but it’s not hard to slide it into a corner when you’re done.

Overall it’s a solidly-made decent piece of kit that’s flexible enough for a good range of exercises. It’s nothing special but seems pretty competitive compared to other incline benches and the decline option gives it an extra bit of functionality that some don’t have.

Review: Nice little workout bench, I say little it’s full size haha. Took about 10 minutes to build, has bits on the back to place any weights you buy separately. Fairly thick cushion wrapped in nice and easy to wipe fake leather. Just a simple universal bench which could house many of workouts ! Came in handy as just purchased a treadmill and wobble machine. Product: JX FITNESS Power Tower Adjustable Dip Station Pull up Bar Push Up Workout Abdominal Exercise Home Gym Tower Body Building
Review:
From the title you can guess what I was most impressed with and although it sounds mundane I just liked the attention to detail. It was mostly the shadow board approach to the nuts and bolts of which there are quiet a few varieties. Each bunch of nuts and bolts were separated on a shrink wrapped sheet with the size next to them. The instructions themselves were clear and logical.

Anyway, the actual frame. It certainly is sturdy enough although I'm pretty light but it seems plenty strong enough. The build quality was pretty good and I was impressed with the welds and parts matched up almost correctly in most cases. There were a few holes that weren't exactly right but once it was all tightened up it was fine.

The location of the bar makes pull ups odd if you're facing the back rest pad so you need to do them facing away in order to not bump off of anything. Personally I'd prefer a larger overhang so I could face the back but maybe that's just me. Dips are fine as are leg raises as you would on any tower. The grips for leg raises are good but I don't know why they didn't put any for the dip grips. There is a knurled pattern for the pull up bar but I'd prefer proper grip so I just used grip tape which is fine now.

The pads are nice enough and it's been outside for a few weeks now and I will cover them if it rains. As it weirldy hasn't rained in weeks now it's mid-April I can't comment on how well it stands the weather but as there's no exposed metal without a good thick layer of paint my guess is it'll fare well. I would have it in the garage but I've run out of room with kids bikes etc there now.

I got this just before the COVID 19 lock down pretty much on a whim and now that we're stuck training in our gardens and fitness equipment is in high demand I'm really glad I have it. It helps me to have easy access to just jump on and do some pull ups so I'm getting them done little and often and keep ticking over.

Product: YOLEO Adjustable Weight Bench - Utility Weight Benches for Full Body Workout, Foldable Incline/Decline Bench Press for Home Gym
Review:
I bought this having read some decent reviews : however , I was extremely disappointed with it and now wonder if those who are raving about it have actually ever done any weight lifting before because for my experience - it’s dismal.

Firstly the elastic cables have virtually no resistance whatsoever and are way too long. You would need to be 12 feet tall with a 4 meter wing span to get anything from them . I took them off from the get go.

Thinking it would be ok as a bench , the main reason I bought it I set it up . Construction was simple enough but the built product is useless.

It’s billed as able to recline and decline into 7 variants respectively . Firstly - it doesn’t go into a flat bench . Well it does but literally the weight of my little finger is enough for it to come crashing down . It inclines ok into 2 positions - but anything below that (including flat bench and decline) and it collapses- the ridges on the back pin do not sit safely into the corresponding slots so any weight at all - gravity takes over and it collapses . Common sense evaded the makers when this was designed . It simply isn’t fit for purpose .

It’s billed as safe for up to 330lbs - I weigh at most 215 and whilst pressing a moderate 15kg reverse fly (which is around 33lbs) - it collapsed sending me crashing to the floor with the bells in hand . Thank god it wasn’t the bar bell loaded up because they would have had law suit on their hands

Avoid like the plague if you are a serious lifter . This is not safe .

Product: YOLEO Adjustable Weight Bench - Utility Weight Benches for Full Body Workout, Foldable Incline/Decline Bench Press for Home Gym
Review:
Honest Review:

Positives:
1) Good Bench- feels good enough quality to last long
2) Good quality padding
3)Very sturdy
4) Storage- Folds away to some extend, not as neatly as shown on pictures
4) Assembly- Very easy to assembly and reassembly after collapsed

Negatives
1) Very high off the ground
2) Doesn’t fully straighten for shoulder press
4) All the same width throughout- would be better if it narrowed near top of shoulders
3) Price- they are continuously increasing the price. I paid £100 which I think was overpriced. Reasonable price would be somewhere in the £60 range max
4) Would be better if the the mechanism to raise the bench was as per standard gym benches I.e. bracket with holes in to adjust

Overall: Good bench, worth a purchase but you get what you pay for in this price range. Probably the best of the bunch in terms of what is available right now. Considering gyms not likely to open for a few months yet worth if you have the money and need a bench that will store away go for it! It’s not gym level standard but it’s better than nothing!

Product: YOLEO Adjustable Weight Bench - Utility Weight Benches for Full Body Workout, Foldable Incline/Decline Bench Press for Home Gym
Review: The only good thing I can say is that it arrived four weeks earlier than quoted. Although really only being cosmetic problems for the price it should be perfect,one of the legs had quite a lot of paint missing off it so instead of finishing it properly they touched it up with a different colour black which makes it stand out even more,and also the back pad has been fitted not flush,straight with the base so it's not straight,really poor workmanship for the price of the item,would not recommend.

Product: YOLEO Adjustable Weight Bench - Utility Weight Benches for Full Body Workout, Foldable Incline/Decline Bench Press for Home Gym
Review: So firstly good points.  It's easy to assemble and easy to adjust.  It's not difficult to fold, but a little fiddley (you have to turn it on it's side and remove 3 pins to fold - not the end of the world by any means).Now the bad points.  Firstly he resistance bands that it comes with are just a waste of time.  The resistance is next to nothing and they are ridiculously long.  Next and my biggest bug-bear is that it is just a bit too high off the floor, probably by about an inch or so; this may not seem like a lot but when you're used to "normal" gym equipment, it feels weird.  This can be resolve by placing your feet on the bar that act as the feet, but means you always need to have a close stance as opposed to open stance when exercising.  Thirdly, the back does go completely flat, there's either a small incline or small decline when in the closest positions to being flat; again not the end of the world, but a little annoying.  Lastly, although I've not come across any problems so far, the "hooks" that keep the back rest in place (inclined/declined) don't feel very secure - it doesn't feel like it would take much for it to slip and end up with a face full of barbell....All in all, I use this piece of kit, it was cheap compared to the others available, but I wouldn't get again if I was to buy another - I'd probably go for a better quality one

Product: H&S Ab Abdominal Exercise Roller With Extra Thick Knee Pad Mat - Body Fitness Strength Training Machine AB Wheel Gym Tool
Review:
There's now an innumerable amount of different ab rollers available in the marketplace, I guess because they've become a tried and tested way in which to effectively strengthen and build those abdominal muscles. So, I spent a very long time looking at the pros and cons of those being sold on Amazon, before eventually deciding that for my money, this one from H&S was the best available. Now that I've had it for a few days, I'm beginning to realise this one was a wise choice.

It arrived nicely packaged in a shallow cardboard box. Inside were two wheels, two handles (one with an inner metal tube). These components simply slide together on that chromed tube in a matter of seconds. A nice feature is that, for travel purposes, they can just as easily be disassembled to lay flat in a suitcase. You also get a decent rectangular floor mat, which is essential for protecting those knees.

By the way, there is no 'magic' exercise/machine to give you that sometimes elusive six-pack - using a variety of stomach exercises is key (and doing them in strict style) together with a 'clean' diet, and the ability to burn off those calories if you are prone to easily gain weight. The idea is to try and subtly build those abdominal muscles, but at the same time reduce the layer of fat covering them, so they become prominent - giving the washboard effect.

I train in a gym four times each week, and use a stomach crunch machine plus old-fashioned sit-ups at the end of each workout. I bought this wheel primarily to do extra abdominal exercises at home during my days off.

I've found this to be an excellent ab wheel and is, in my opinion, better than the ones they let us use at my local gym. I've tried it on differing flooring and have found it to have a surprisingly good grip on any surface - I've used it on carpet, vinyl, laminated flooring and ceramic tiles. It is VERY IMPORTANT to use this correctly though - that way you'll avoid potential injury and also achieve optimum results. The supplier sensibly directs buyers to the wikiHow website (ref: Use-an-Ab-Roller) which offers easy-to-understand instructions. There are also many good videos available on YouTube (where would we be without it?) - the two I can recommend are: Ab Wheel Extension by Bodylastics and Ab Wheel For Beginners by Minus The Gym. Use it the right way, and use it regularly and you may well find this is one of the best (and cheapest) investments you've ever made. If you have found this review of use please be sure to click on the 'Helpful' button below 🏋🏽💪😊

Product: H&S Ab Abdominal Exercise Roller With Extra Thick Knee Pad Mat - Body Fitness Strength Training Machine AB Wheel Gym Tool
Review: Not as sturdy as photos. There is a big gap between the two wheels, which I tried for 20 mins to close thinking I’ve done something wrong. Reading some other reviews this is a common problem with this poor design. The gap in between the two wheels makes the whole thing wobbly when you are trying to roll it. Very poorly designed. I’m glad to have a refund from Amazon. Honestly go look at Decathlon’s ab roller for £5.99 and you’ll see it’s so much better.

Product: H&S Ab Abdominal Exercise Roller With Extra Thick Knee Pad Mat - Body Fitness Strength Training Machine AB Wheel Gym Tool

Product: H&S Ab Abdominal Exercise Roller With Extra Thick Knee Pad Mat - Body Fitness Strength Training Machine AB Wheel Gym Tool
Review:
Saw an exercise video and the guy said he only uses an ab roller so I was sold.

Quickly looked on Amazon and this one had some decent reviews for a reasonable price so I ordered. The item comes in a much smaller box than I expected. It took about 30 seconds to assemble it, you do need to have some strength to push the components together.

Once assembled it's small size doesn't work against it at all. It's really effective. It also comes with a small foam knee pad to save your knees.

I did 20 roll-outs and the next day my upper abs were definitely engaged as I could feel it, the good pain you get when you know a muscle group has been worked effectively.

Only one caveat is that I wouldn't use it on carpet as it seems to quickly flatten it into a groove. Hard floors only.

Review: I use the wheels every morning as part of my exercise routine, I have made one modification to them as you can fit the wheels on the metal tube in two ways, one way pushes the wheels against each other which makes it too narrow and a bit wobbly the other way allows the wheels to wander a bit on the metal tube so I have cut a bit of plastic tubing to a 1inch/ 25mm length and put it between the wheels which makes them about 2inches/50mm apart which I find is much better and more stable.

At home, you do need a hook to attach it to. I bought the following from Amazon and attached it to a beam:

https://amzn.to/3cfp7YL

With all these types of equipment, it's a case of just doing it and you'll get the result. Diet obviously plays a bigger part than just exercise. So if you are looking to tone up and lose weight you'll need to consider a lifestyle change to get the results you want.

whislt the suspension trainer is good quality and easy to set up/get to grips with.

I tried to register the straps in Jan 2020 (purchased in early Dec 2019) customer service took a week reply, only to tell me that the serial number was not on their database. still awaiting updates two weeks later.

also the official TRX mobile app is incredably poor. despite me registering an account i cant never log in meaning again no access to any official content.

you expect to have the security of customer service when you buy official products at higher cost. at this point im thinking I might as well have bought a cheaper alternative

Product: WINNOW Adjustable Weight Bench with Dip Station Folding Heavy Duty Weight Lifting Bench Home Training Gym Multiuse Workout Bench
Review:
OK so Ive been using Gyms for 15yrs+, and since lockdown I needed a home bench.

I settled on this one for cost, and availability. Overall, if you want a basic home bench to get started with weights, or maintain where you at then this is a good bench. If you are already lifting heavy and really want to push yourself, then this aint the bench for you.

Im 6.2', 90kgs, and benching 70-100kgs and its all fits / works fine - the hand grip position is the main issue as covered below.

Pros'
- very easy to build, took about 30 mins.
- Sturdy, it doesn't wobble or shake when in use like other home benches I've used.
- Dip handles are a nice addition
- folds away easy to save space
- Quick delivery - was about 10days faster than stated on Amazon.

Cons
- The support bars for holding the barbell, are in the exact place you want to hold the bar, meaning that you have to adjust your grip once you have lifted the bar. This is not great, and prevents you from going to your max weight.
- One of the support bars was damaged - the metal is bent, its only cosmetic, but looks like a factory defect and is a little annoying.
- Overpriced - though not as much as most. With covid 19 all gym equipment costs a bomb now, I have seen similar benches to this online for £150 - £300. Really I would say that this is worth £40-£50 but given the circs, I was happy to pay £80.
- The 'incline' mode is a little poor. Rather than the end of the bench where you head is being raised, you just drop the end of the bench where you but is, meaning you end up half on the floor. Not ideal, however until the gyms reopen it will do for now.

Ultimately it is an average HOME gym bench, that I don't regret buying. However if you are expecting the kind of bench that you use in the gym, this is not it. Dont expect to be lifting more that 100kgs on this... however if you are new to weight lifting then this is a great starting bench.

Product: WINNOW Adjustable Weight Bench with Dip Station Folding Heavy Duty Weight Lifting Bench Home Training Gym Multiuse Workout Bench
Review: I found it easy to put together. Take your time, unpack it all first and read the instructions... It's not hard.It is surprisingly light and easy to move. Folds nicely and is good if, like me, you have limited space.It's quite sturdy and well made.One downside. If you're tall/very big I'm not sure this is the right bench for you. Being 5' 8' it's OK for me. I bought it for my chest workout and it's great for that.

Product: WINNOW Adjustable Weight Bench with Dip Station Folding Heavy Duty Weight Lifting Bench Home Training Gym Multiuse Workout Bench
Review: The bench arrived very quickly (next day) and is a good solid bench; not too difficult to put together, and for the money a great bench. However, I was looking for a bench that can be adjusted to an incline position, which I found this bench couldn’t do correctly. There’s 2 hooks for an incline bar to go, but this is nowhere near enough room for my head to go below the barbell. For this reason I will be returning.The bench in general though can’t be knocked; for the money it’s very good value. Unfortunately incline is a necessity for me, but if you’re only looking to flat bench, this is the bench for you.

Product: WINNOW Adjustable Weight Bench with Dip Station Folding Heavy Duty Weight Lifting Bench Home Training Gym Multiuse Workout Bench
Review: This weight bench is by no means a professional gym item, however, it’s ideal for a beginner, with a medium build, who wants to do some general exercise at home. It’s sturdy and easy to assemble. It doesn’t take up much space and can be folded away after use, which is great for storage. I have a 55lbs barbell which this entry-level bench holds well.

Product: WINNOW Adjustable Weight Bench with Dip Station Folding Heavy Duty Weight Lifting Bench Home Training Gym Multiuse Workout Bench
Review:
I bought this bench to use at home while the gyms are closed and to avoid the mad rush after they re-open.

The bench was easy enough to put together and feels sturdy.

The main reason for me only giving it 3/5 stars is due to the placement of the beams which hold the barbell.
Unfortunately the beams hold the bar exactly where I'd grip the bar, meaning I have to use a wider / smaller grip on the bar and reducing the amount I can safely life, due to having to adjust my grip.

The poor placement of the beams also make it difficult to put the bar back down, since I have to adjust my grip again beforehand. If I had to put the bar down quickly, I'd be unable to do so without crushing my hands between either the proper holders or the little black fixed holders designed to catch the bar if I dropped it on myself.

Review: I use them in my classes and my clients “love to hate them” 😂 Brilliant, but just wish they had burpees on it. In fact, if it lands on the black logo, I get them to do burpees anyway. 😆

Product: Phoenix Fitness RY1051 Exercise Dice for Workout Fun - Fitness Decision Dice - Switch Up Training Routines, HIIT and Exercises - Home and Gym - Orange
Review:
Excellent piece of kit and great fun. Description doesn't say what is on the dice so I'll fill you in:
Dice 1: 10 Reps, 20 Reps, 30 Reps, 30 seconds, 60 seconds, 90 seconds.

Dice 2: Jumping Jack's, Press Ups, Crunches, Lunge Walks, Squats, Phoenix Fitness Logo

Me and my wife use these for circuit training taking turns to roll them. Makes it easier to blame the other one if you end up with 90 seconds of your least favourite exercise.

If it lands on the logo we rest for the length of time the other dice lands on or do burpees if it lands on it too early in the workout.

We are both into our gym and fitness and a 30 minute workout with these is very hard work and leaves you very tired and sore the next day (though I guess it depends how hard yu work...). I also use them as a 10 min warmup before doing something else. Save me having to think about what I want to do or "cheat" and give myself something easy. It's up to the dice.

I did think they might lack versatility, but you can switch it up by thinking "if it lands on press ups I'll pick up some dumbells for arm curls" etc.

I would definitely recommend these.

Product: Wonder Core 2 with built in Twisting Seat and Rower
Review: After being out of the hardcore exercise game for 6 months i ordered this to start getting back into it and it does everything you could need, So the pro's: Locking the back rest in a half locked position and doing 30 minutes of sit ups leaves you feeling like you have been sucker punched in the gut for the first few days but it quickly goes and you can up the amount you do, The rowing system does work very well and you feel the burn on your arms as there are atleast 6 different ways to use them to completely work out the lower arms upper arms shoulders stomach cheat and back with these, The cons: with the rowing system is i would like to see a tension adjuster on it to up the difficulty as after a while it becomes to easy doing one thing. Same as the rowing i would like to have seen an adjustment ability on the back rest to give more tension for situps i prefer half locked so the second half of sitting up is all me but i have seen this on other similar products and that would be a big improvement,  it would also be easier to do straight situps it the seat had a lock on it as it tends to move to the left or right which can become irritating after a while. The only other con is the central lock on the frame is not the best making it quick wobbly could be improved. Overall a great machine for anyone from novice to experienced with this type of exercise i would advise anyone to try but with the adjustments noted above this would be a 5 star all rounder.

Product: Wonder Core 2 with built in Twisting Seat and Rower
Review: Superb piece of fitness equipment . Ideal for a home user who is not likely to visit a gym. I have used it for a month EVERY day and can certainly tell the difference. A lo g way of a six pack but certainly you g up, The DVD showing exercises is a really good addition. Three modes of exercises. I can now manage the boot camp version.I do not think a regular gym user would be to impressed, bit for the arm chair fitness guy it is IDEAL.100% satisfied.

Product: Wonder Core 2 with built in Twisting Seat and Rower
Review: With all the gym closures, due to obvious covid reasons, I was in the market for a bench. I stumbled across this while researching and I'm glad I did! This primarily is to help with the core physique of the body, don't be fooled, just using this won't get you the body that you see in the pics and videos BUT for under £100, it's a bargain! The sit-up range of motion is great! And the resistance bands are of good quality and can aid a good warm up. The great advantage for me is I double this up to use as a bench, which when I've coupled with weights, can actually get a massive range of exercises. It's light and easy to put together. Good small footprint so doesn't use too much space in the room and folds up easily to store (even though I just leave mine out). Would recommend 100% it lives up to expectations

Product: Wonder Core 2 with built in Twisting Seat and Rower

Review: After reading the different (mixed) reviews I was a little bit unsure about whether these were any good or not, so, after some research I decided to buy the medium "Pro" gripz.I was fully prepared to struggle with my normal weights during my workout routine and thought I would have to reduce the weight but, I was able to complete my workout with the same weight. Product: Fat Gripz Pro - The Simple Proven Way to Get Big Biceps & Forearms Fast (Winner of The Men’s Health Magazine Home Gym Award 2020) (2.25" Outer Diameter)
Review: Brilliant product, I am a newbie to weights and lifting, however the new dumbbells that I got had too narrow of a grip on them. Being 5'11 and having quite big hands I needed something with a nice wide grip and these were absolutely perfect. All the other benefits that come with using fat gripz is a bonus for me. I love them and so does my partner. Not the cheapest but a very valuable investment. The product its self looks and feels high quality and so far so good. The personal emails from the company was a lovely touch especially giving hints and tips and even some suggested exercises. Brilliant fat gripz thank you.

Product: Fat Gripz Pro - The Simple Proven Way to Get Big Biceps & Forearms Fast (Winner of The Men’s Health Magazine Home Gym Award 2020) (2.25" Outer Diameter)
Review:
Have just resumed using these after a long time, since losing my old pair of Fat Gripz, primarily to enhance grip strength. While I cannot speak with absolute certainty as to their effectiveness in terms of improving grip strength, one definitely gets a better pump in the arms.

I like the prduct because it is heavy duty and user friendly, and I'm inclined to say good value for money due to the fact that they have the potential to literally last you a lifetime, be bequeathed to your progeny, and then last a few more.

They're a good tool to add a form of resistance to your existing training protocol, thereby making your sessions in the gym more challenging.

If your goal is to increase the size of your forearms then these should be a requisite peace of weaponry to carry around in your gym bag. They easily fit over most dumbbell handles, as well as barbell and chin up bars, and can be used in a variety of ways and beyond, just be creative if you happen to run out of the more conventional ones. If you get tired of using these then taking a break won't hurt since they're not likely to expire before you decide to revisit.

Product: Fat Gripz Pro - The Simple Proven Way to Get Big Biceps & Forearms Fast (Winner of The Men’s Health Magazine Home Gym Award 2020) (2.25" Outer Diameter)
Review: I was asked to rate these on comfort as well as other factors and almost rated them low for comfort... but it's kinda the point! Look, they are about as comfy as they're going to get - but due to the nature of them, they make holding onto weights a fairly difficult experience, particularly for certain exercises / muscle groups. They really do seem to work though. Especially on chest exercises, I felt like I was hitting parts I'd never hit before when using these.

Product: Fat Gripz Pro - The Simple Proven Way to Get Big Biceps & Forearms Fast (Winner of The Men’s Health Magazine Home Gym Award 2020) (2.25" Outer Diameter)
Review: I have held off leaving a review until I could give these gripz a real trial and I personally wouldn't be without them now!What a difference these gripz make, it literally intensifies the workout engaging muscles that may of been harder to hit on a standard bar.As soon as you pick the barbell or dumbell up with the Fat Gripz on you can feel the difference. If you want a stronger grip then get some of these, if you want a harder workout and more bang for your buck, get a set of these, you won't be dissapointed! Thanks Matt for the Fat Gripz and the workout tips tht you took time to email after the purchase, appreciate it.

Product: Fat Gripz Pro - The Simple Proven Way to Get Big Biceps & Forearms Fast (Winner of The Men’s Health Magazine Home Gym Award 2020) (2.25" Outer Diameter)
Review: I can’t believe I haven’t written a review for these yet. I’ve had them for something over three years now and they are absolutely fantastic. Still holding up perfectly and showing no signs of wear whatsoever. If you want to get a stronger grip, buy these, they will completely change your workouts and they will suck at first, but it is shocking how quickly you’ll notice a difference with consistent use. They won’t make much of a difference if you don’t use them consistently though and that requires dropping whatever weights you’re currently working with, but it will come back up quickly and you’ll fly by whatever plateaus you’ve been stuck at before now.Speaking for the product itself they are solid  as all get out, you could probably drive over them with a tank and they’d come out looking new. They fit all grips around the size of one inch and if it is slightly too large for the fat gripz the just expand to fit onto the bar anyways and will just be slightly larger than two inches. All in all absolutely worth the money, and I would say one if the best purchases I have ever made.Happy lifting!

Product: Fat Gripz Pro - The Simple Proven Way to Get Big Biceps & Forearms Fast (Winner of The Men’s Health Magazine Home Gym Award 2020) (2.25" Outer Diameter)
Review: In my opinion, there is nothing to dislike. I have never pulled the trigger on and I greatly regret it. I have have up to 25lbs adjustable dumbells, the fat grip make it feel more like 35lbs. Which is great cause obviously without them i dont have access to that kind of weight. Now the pump (without vasodilator is awesome) there is nothing better than then banging about curl after curl and watching the vein in your arms enlarge. I have yet to try them with pull ups or any machine but with the gyms opening back up I cannot wait! You I have the blue set which I think is 1.75 and I'm gonna give it a few months before I size up.

Product: Fat Gripz Pro - The Simple Proven Way to Get Big Biceps & Forearms Fast (Winner of The Men’s Health Magazine Home Gym Award 2020) (2.25" Outer Diameter)
Review: Do to these unforeseen times I have been in the market to find needed supplies for a simple home gym. These are on the top of my list. They are top quality and are so simply to use.  Not only can I use them on my dumb bells to work on my grip and forearm strength but also on my bands for an extra grip. I will bring these everywhere I go to work out now. Also the Fat Gripz team came in contact with me via email and game me a work out plan and tips on how to improve my workouts. I am so proud to be part of the Fat Gripz family.

Product: Fat Gripz Pro - The Simple Proven Way to Get Big Biceps & Forearms Fast (Winner of The Men’s Health Magazine Home Gym Award 2020) (2.25" Outer Diameter)
Review: Certainly a different impact to the arms, and will increase grip strength. I've use them for bicep curls and dumbell presses thus far, and it's definitely a way to shock your muscle group and change the target area, or at the very least widen the targeted area to the forearms and overall hand grip strength.

Product: Fat Gripz Pro - The Simple Proven Way to Get Big Biceps & Forearms Fast (Winner of The Men’s Health Magazine Home Gym Award 2020) (2.25" Outer Diameter)
Review: Fat Gripz are a brilliant idea.  The first time I set them up on my pullup bar and did some dead hangs I could immediately feel how they recruit additional muscle in my forearms, and perhaps surprisingly I could feel it throughout my arms and shoulders as well. You can use them for just about any dumbell or barbell exercise as well, and I've also found them great to reduce the stress on my palms during dips.

Product: Fat Gripz Pro - The Simple Proven Way to Get Big Biceps & Forearms Fast (Winner of The Men’s Health Magazine Home Gym Award 2020) (2.25" Outer Diameter)
Review: Works well. The new look is great. No issues with comfort or durability. There was a review complaining about it being too squishy but I didn’t experience that at all. It might compress a tiny bit at the very edge where the material tapers out but it doesn’t impact the performance and effectiveness. I use these grips as I work up in the deadlift and as my grip starts to fail I move down to the series one and finally just the bar. Forearms are pretty beat after this.

Product: Fat Gripz Pro - The Simple Proven Way to Get Big Biceps & Forearms Fast (Winner of The Men’s Health Magazine Home Gym Award 2020) (2.25" Outer Diameter)
Review: These things are amazing. When I first used I had to drop my dumbell biceps curls from 55 lbs to 40 lbs and felt my arms working much more. In fact the next day my arms were more sore than they have been in years. Fat gripz can also be used for chest, shoulders, back and triceps. I definitely feel my muscles working much harder everytime I use them. Make sure you purchase the original fat gripz as I have used all the replicas and they do don't compare.

Product: Fat Gripz Pro - The Simple Proven Way to Get Big Biceps & Forearms Fast (Winner of The Men’s Health Magazine Home Gym Award 2020) (2.25" Outer Diameter)
Review: 15min in and my hand is shaking, even my pinky got a workout. My forearm is swollen even from not having any preworkout or supplement. A must buy. I have not tried any other brands but this works!

Product: Fat Gripz Pro - The Simple Proven Way to Get Big Biceps & Forearms Fast (Winner of The Men’s Health Magazine Home Gym Award 2020) (2.25" Outer Diameter)
Review: Most people who buy these are likely doing so with "heavier" weights, but as someone who is only able to lift light weights at high reps, Fat Gripz provides an additonal challenge and greater direct and indirect muscle contraction that would otherwise not be present.The outer surface is quite grippy and they're made of a very durable material. I can't speak to using these on heavy compound movements, but they add a great additional contraction at lower weights, as I'm sure they do with heavier weights. Recommended.

Product: Fat Gripz Pro - The Simple Proven Way to Get Big Biceps & Forearms Fast (Winner of The Men’s Health Magazine Home Gym Award 2020) (2.25" Outer Diameter)
Review: Usually people buy these Fat Gripz to strengthen their grip, (I don't know what some people are talking about when they say that they had to drop weight because it was harder, but I didn't have to drop weight). I have noticed an increase in my grip and my forearms get a decent amount of soreness the day after a good workout. But the main reason I had decided to get these Fat Gripz is because all of the my knuckles in my hands had been hurting for a long time when I did my dumbbell workouts. so I figured my bigger hands needed bigger hand grips that would lessen the pain in my knuckles, turns out I was right. Gripping the small bars on the dumbbells always hurt and I would have to put down the weights every few minutes. I can say now that since I have been using these Fat Gripz, the knuckles in my hands do not hurt during my dumbbell workouts and I am grateful. I think they sell bigger ones and I'll probably get them to do some harder grip strengthening.I put 4 stars on easy to use because getting them on/off dumbbells can sometimes be slightly difficult depending how wore out you are from your workout. Anyway for Cap dumbbells that you get from Walmart or Academy the bars for the dumbbells get thicker past like 20ish pounds. There is a 1.5ish gap when you put them on the 40lb ones. There is no slipping of the weights and its more comfortable than it sounds.

Product: Fat Gripz Pro - The Simple Proven Way to Get Big Biceps & Forearms Fast (Winner of The Men’s Health Magazine Home Gym Award 2020) (2.25" Outer Diameter)
Review:
Yo!! Like most of you, I too was skeptical of spending this much on some gym gear. I've watched a ton of reviews and gym athlete feedbacks on this product and unfortunately was still iffy on it. Until one day, I got in a gnarly gym session with a buddy of mine who had them. He suggested that I should try it and DAM. After going through the entire first set of the workout, I can see why people speak highly of this product. I knew instantly that this has gotta be a gym necessity that needs to be in my bag. Ever since I've gotten this, I began to incorporate it in a lot of my pull workouts as well as arm workouts. I can already tell that my grip strength is increasing remarkably and I'm always finding new ways to throw them into my workouts.

The great thing is that once you buy the product, theres a unique workout manual that shows you the most effective workout to maximize the use of Fat Gripz. For its price, you can certainly tell the quality of this product is high and I know it's gonna last me a while. 10/10 would highly recommend!

Side note: it also makes you look beast AF at the gym training with Fat Gripz. And I know a lot of yall wanna look beastly, sooo... What're ya waiting for?!

Product: Fat Gripz Pro - The Simple Proven Way to Get Big Biceps & Forearms Fast (Winner of The Men’s Health Magazine Home Gym Award 2020) (2.25" Outer Diameter)
Review: Overall the feel is great. And it dosnt have any give like I was expecting. However they do not fit around a standard Olympic power bar. So there is roughly a gap 1” large. Meaning the actual size is more close to 3.25” vs it’s stated size of2.25”  This isn’t necessarily a bad thing. But the fact there is such a big gap makes it very difficult to get a proper Handel on something so large. Meaning you have to have your hand in basically one specific spot to not have the large gap dig into your hands and cause instability or discomfort. Overall they feel super sturdy and I’m sure they will last for years and years. But the fact they don’t fit around normal/common bars properly is a big negative and makes them not optimal to use effectively and safely. But if you can get around that problem and take the time to position your hand in that one goldy locks spot then they are great.

Product: Fat Gripz Pro - The Simple Proven Way to Get Big Biceps & Forearms Fast (Winner of The Men’s Health Magazine Home Gym Award 2020) (2.25" Outer Diameter)
Review:
When I first bought the fat gripz I honestly thought they were just another scam product that wouldn't provide any real benefit. Boy was I surprised by the very first workout.

I incorporated the Fat Gripz into our volume day workout by adding it pretty much to every exercise. We started with banded face pulls, banded straight arm pull downs, and banded upright rows. I simply put the Fat Gripz on the band near our normal hand placement and we went to work. We do 3 sets of 20 reps on these 3 exercises in a cycle with a minute rest between cycles. Typically there is no strain in the forearm during these exercises. At the end of the first cycle my forearms were on fire...fully pumped. I actually struggled to complete the 3 cycles because I could barely grip the Fat Gripz. I was able to complete the rest of the workout but I had to add some additional rest time for my forearms between exercises.

After my first workout I decided that it might be a good idea to read the instructions and realized that I may have over done it a bit. We've now been using the Fat Gripz for about 2 months and have consistently incorporated them into out workout in the manner described in the instructions. I have noticed a significant increase in forearm and arm strength. I've also noted a significant increase in vascularization (bigger and more visible veins) of the forearms.

I was so impressed that I bought 3 more pairs of Fat Gripz so that I could leave them on certain pieces of equipment that we regularly use them on. The only difficult part I found was changing them from one piece of equipment to the next during the workout when your forearms are pumped. When your forearms are not pumped it isn't an issue but I did struggle a bit with fully pumped forearms thus the purchase of add'l pairs to avoid having to change them as often.

Highly recommended for anyone that is serious about full body training. This will allow you to work your forearms without having to add add'l exercises specific for the forearms and will help you get more out of those exercises that are specifically for the forearms.

Product: Fat Gripz Pro - The Simple Proven Way to Get Big Biceps & Forearms Fast (Winner of The Men’s Health Magazine Home Gym Award 2020) (2.25" Outer Diameter)
Review:
I've been a weight lifter for about 20 years. My forearms are fairly strong (e.g., I can do shrugs with up to 140lbs dumbbells in each arm without any straps / hooks). That said, these things make my forearms burn like never before!

I've been using them for about a week now for all exercises. I am incredibly impressed. I ordered two sets: one for my barbell and one for my adjustable weight dumbbells. This way, I just keep them on the bars at all times. There is absolutely no question that my forearms are getting worked out like never before; I don't recall them ever being this sore.

If you want to increase your forearm strength, which truly is a bottleneck for so many exercises (e.g., wide grip pull ups, lat pull downs, shrugs, deadlifts, dumbbell calve raises, etc.), you *need* to try this. They are also incredibly well built. They ring of a world-class craftmanship.. I'll probably order a few more pairs, just because.

Product: Fat Gripz Pro - The Simple Proven Way to Get Big Biceps & Forearms Fast (Winner of The Men’s Health Magazine Home Gym Award 2020) (2.25" Outer Diameter)
Review: I was a little hesitant to spend the $40, but after receiving them and using them I believe it is worth the expense. The packaging was great. The overall construction seems excellent. The rubber like material is very heavy and built to last.I’ve been dealing with tennis elbow for while now. I found that when using these grips I can drop down the weight of the dumbbells about 10 pounds from what I normally use (down to 40lbs). I still seem to hit my biceps just as hard if not harder with less weight and have less strain on my elbows. Also, it works you’re forearms and grip strength at the same time. I’m sure if you used these with reverse grip curls, your forearms would be on fire! Unfortunately,iIt’s too much strain on my elbows to try those right now.

Product: Fat Gripz Pro - The Simple Proven Way to Get Big Biceps & Forearms Fast (Winner of The Men’s Health Magazine Home Gym Award 2020) (2.25" Outer Diameter)
Review:
Try it on pull-up bars, kettle bells, plates, I even snapped them onto a sledge hammer for field day.
They are dang tough, make me ache from my palms up to my elbows (them good gains pains, friend).
My grip feels compromised and weak after using these, and after a couple weeks of use - take them off and try the same lifts... you’ll fly!
They are as good as your imagination - snap them onto anything that even resembles a bar (like a safe sturdy tree branch, just look around champ) and see how your arms open up.

There is value in a gentle handshake - this tool can make you forget all about that though!

Product: Fat Gripz Pro - The Simple Proven Way to Get Big Biceps & Forearms Fast (Winner of The Men’s Health Magazine Home Gym Award 2020) (2.25" Outer Diameter)
Review: Very good product.  Well designed. Sturdy.  Does exactly what you'd expect it to do.  Remains to be seen what sorts of benefits I'll gain from it.  But I can totally see the upside to mixing it into one's workouts.  I'm not sure how much overall muscle isolating it does.  But it definitely activates the forearms.  For that alone, it's well worth the price.  Can't imagine what the super size version is like. The standard size is pretty hefty (to grasp, that is)

Product: Fat Gripz Pro - The Simple Proven Way to Get Big Biceps & Forearms Fast (Winner of The Men’s Health Magazine Home Gym Award 2020) (2.25" Outer Diameter)

A Must Buy

Product: Fat Gripz Pro - The Simple Proven Way to Get Big Biceps & Forearms Fast (Winner of The Men’s Health Magazine Home Gym Award 2020) (2.25" Outer Diameter)
Review: I am loving the fat grips, they are so thick and firm and they feel great on my hands. At first they are really tight so I had to work a bit to get the slit to come apart and then I just gently slide them onto the shaft of my barbells or curling bar. Feeling the thick diameter around the palm of my hands is amazing and helps me obtain a real strong and massive pump. It really works my muscles and intensifies my workouts so much more that I can see my veins budging from my forearms as I feel the deep burning sensation in my biceps as I slowly curl my arms up and down controlling the weights every second of the time. I can pretty quickly  reach the climax of my workout a lot sooner than I usually would. I recommend these to everyone.

Product: Fat Gripz Pro - The Simple Proven Way to Get Big Biceps & Forearms Fast (Winner of The Men’s Health Magazine Home Gym Award 2020) (2.25" Outer Diameter)

Product: Fat Gripz Pro - The Simple Proven Way to Get Big Biceps & Forearms Fast (Winner of The Men’s Health Magazine Home Gym Award 2020) (2.25" Outer Diameter)
Review: I suppose these grips would protect your hands from callous formation, but they are much too massive to be comfortable for the vast majority female lifters, and how many serious male lifters really care about that?Otherwise, these are bulky and uncomfortable. It might help if they reduced the outside diameter of the grips, but I suspect that the same results could be achieved by simply increasing the weight by a few pounds.

Product: Fat Gripz Pro - The Simple Proven Way to Get Big Biceps & Forearms Fast (Winner of The Men’s Health Magazine Home Gym Award 2020) (2.25" Outer Diameter)
Review: I have always thought I had larger than average hands and the blue medium size were pretty much pushing the extent of my ability to grip these but they put a burn on your forearms that is hard to match otherwise. As others stated it will lower your weight limit until you get used to the pump but I switch them off and on dumbell handles during my sets and it's really not a big deal. Product: Fat Gripz Pro - The Simple Proven Way to Get Big Biceps & Forearms Fast (Winner of The Men’s Health Magazine Home Gym Award 2020) (2.25" Outer Diameter)

Product: PROIRON 20kg Cast Iron Adjustable Dumbbell Set Hand Weight with Solid Dumbbell Handles Changed into Barbell Handily Perfect for Bodybuilding Fitness Weight Lifting Training Home Gym
Review: If you have used weights in a gym, you will find these weights perfectly familiar. The advantage is that you can vary the amount of weight on each short bar and even use the connecting tube in either of two ways to make them into one barbell. After a few weeks of lockdown, I intend to start with them at about 6kg each and slowly build up through the summer. Only really strong people who want much heavier weights will find them insufficient. They arrive in a small very solid box which is difficult to carry, both for the courier and then yourself, so you need to exercise caution.If you want to do exercises that require you to swing the weights repeatedly in a lengthwise direction or to twist them while swinging them, then you would probably be better off with fixed dumbbells rather than variable ones like these because with these the ring weights are held in place with a large nut that would work loose with those movements. These are suitable for traditional weight-lifting movements, but you can still find plenty of variety of those movements available. For me they are ideal, but lighter fixed weights would allow those HIIT kinds of exercises more easily.With gyms closed down, and then the issue of whether air-conditioning is safe when they open up, I think these are life-savers. My previous set lasted decades, but I kept them in the garage and they eventually rusted away. I expect these to outlive me by a long time.Also, they were delivered very promptly, ahead of the expected delivery date, by a very strong man who warned me from his van about how heavy the box was - very sensible. I am very glad to have them.

Review: Just received this to find the set is missing 1x 2.5KG weight plate. Only 3x 2.5kg not the 4x as described in the description making the dumbbells unusable as they are not equal weight. Extremely overpriced considering it’s not even a full set

Review: This product seemed a little expensive but had great reviews so I decided to give it a try. Upon inspection the central bar which turns the set into a barbell does not screw onto the dumbbells and it appears that the internal thread has not been formed properly. This is very disappointing as it leaves me with an overpriced set of dumbbells.Other than this, the product seems reasonable. The O-rings aren't a great fit so get pinched over the handles but the spinlock ends don't come loose very often and the quality appears OK.

Product: PROIRON 20kg Cast Iron Adjustable Dumbbell Set Hand Weight with Solid Dumbbell Handles Changed into Barbell Handily Perfect for Bodybuilding Fitness Weight Lifting Training Home Gym
Review:
Building my own home gym having spent the last 10 years training. These are regular spin lock dumbells. The weights are not too big/wide and combine with an existing spin lock set I have quite easily. Build quality is good. Holes in plates are standard spin lock size so would not fit an Olympic bar.

I was surprised about the bar extension. Being honest I thought it would be a bit of a gimmick but it actually works really well. It is suitable for doing many exercises - so far shoulder press, tricep skull crushers narrow grip press etc. It was worked fine for all of them. Nothing heavier that a 20 kg load on each end so far but it feels study enough to take more.

Would recommend.

Product: PROIRON 20kg Cast Iron Adjustable Dumbbell Set Hand Weight with Solid Dumbbell Handles Changed into Barbell Handily Perfect for Bodybuilding Fitness Weight Lifting Training Home Gym
Review: I’ve never reviewed an item so fast. I just received this. Sunday DPD delivery. The box is tiny, and the packaging is spot on. The equipment assembled is sturdy, really strong and easily adjustable. Their are rubber washers that you can buy spare at a hardware store. These allow you really tighten the plates so that there’s not that irritating disk turning movement you can find on cheap tightening mechanism. I’m really happy and thought this merits a review. I’ve been reading and reading about these due to virus. And these cake back on market and there’s no abuse of power with the valuing. Well done.

Product: PROIRON 20kg Cast Iron Adjustable Dumbbell Set Hand Weight with Solid Dumbbell Handles Changed into Barbell Handily Perfect for Bodybuilding Fitness Weight Lifting Training Home Gym
Review:
These are amazing. For £65 it's a great deal.
You might find cheaper on Argos(if you find them on stock) but I'm really happy with the build quality.
There are very tiny imperfections like some of the plates is slightly heavier by 20-80 grams which is not an issue, noway you can tell difference. Although all of them is above the weight advertising which is a good thing, the 2.5KG typically are 2.580 etc.
None of them were lower than advertised.
The middle connector I don't like but I didn't expect it to like it, it lock securely but there is a movement up and down when using it.
Not an issue at all, it's very safe.

Product: PROIRON 20kg Cast Iron Adjustable Dumbbell Set Hand Weight with Solid Dumbbell Handles Changed into Barbell Handily Perfect for Bodybuilding Fitness Weight Lifting Training Home Gym

It's a good max weight for beginners but I'm certain if I need to go past 20kg you can get heavier plates. It's cast iron rather than plastic and sand which makes it more robust and it's comfortable to use. £60 may seem steep, but considering the price of most official gym sets I think you get a good deal.

Overall, a good buy and excellent value for money.

Product: PROIRON 20kg Cast Iron Adjustable Dumbbell Set Hand Weight with Solid Dumbbell Handles Changed into Barbell Handily Perfect for Bodybuilding Fitness Weight Lifting Training Home Gym
Review: Photo compares the prioron (left, grey) to my older current set (right, black). Great solid cast iron set, the screws are smooth and lock together securely with rubber seals to prevent unscrewing while in use (Did arrive in the box still greasy from production but thats not a problem, make sure to clean them so they don't slide off in use). The bar when put together is a perfect width fit for my shoulders, I am quite a slim guy, not sure how it would suit larger taller broader shoulder users.Another reason I have shared it is to show it is a smaller inner diameter compared to other brands. Well made product, recommended
